University Press, 1995. Identity and difference: the European Union and 
postmodernism / Ian Ward -- The language of rights and European integration
/ Grainne de Burca -- The single market: from prima donna to journeyman / 
Damian Chalmers -- The legacy of the market citizen / Michelle Everson -- 
Migrant workers and their families in the European Union: the pervasive 
market ideology of Community law / Tamara K. Hervey -- W(h)ither social 
policy? / Elaine A. Whiteford -- The acquired rights directive: frustrating
or facilitating labour market flexibility / Gilliam More -- The GATT and 
community law: rethinking the "regulatory gap" / Joanne Scott. (continued) 
Regulating the free movement of goods: institutions and institutional 
change / Kenneth A. Armstrong -- Changing patterns of European Community 
utilities law and policy: an institutional hypothesis / Colin Scott -- 
Telecommunications and European integration / Leo Flynn -- Legislative 
review by the EC Commission: revision without radicalism / Imelda Maher -- 
A European litigation strategy: the case of the equal opportunities 
commission / Catherine Barnard -- The Court of Justice: taking taxes 
seriously? / Peter Crowther -- Political theory, law and European union / 
Daniel Wincott. Law -- European Union countries. 

