S. KRISHNAMURTHY. Bangalore, India : R. R. Publishers, 1996. Police -- 
Complaints against -- India. Police and public safety -- India. Law 
enforcement -- India. Human rights -- India. 
<P>
<H5>Japan</H5>
KNX74 .J37 1996. JAPANESE LAW AND LEGAL THEORY / EDITED BY KOICHIRO 
FUJIKURA. New York, NY : New York University Press, 1996. Law -- Japan. 
<P>
<H5>Soviet Union & Former Soviet Union</H5>
KLA1572 .S65 1996. Solomon, Peter H. SOVIET CRIMINAL JUSTICE UNDER STALIN /
PETER H. SOLOMON, JR. Cambridge [England] ; New York : Cambridge University
Press, 1996. Criminal justice, Administration of -- Soviet Union -- 
History. Criminal law -- Soviet Union -- History. Political questions and 
judicial power -- Soviet Union -- History. Soviet Union -- Politics and 
government -- 1936-1953. 
<P>
KLB440 .R87 1996. RUSSIAN LEGAL THEORY / EDITED BY W.E. BUTLER. New York, 
NY : New York University Press, 1996. Law -- Russia (Federation) -- 
Philosophy. Jurisprudence -- Russia (Federation). Law -- Philosophy. 
<P>
<H4>Miscellaneous</H4>
<H5>CD-ROM</H5>
NATIONAL CRIMINAL JUSTICE REFERENCE SERVICE DOCUMENT DATA BASE [COMPUTER
FILE] / U.S. DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE, NATIONAL INSTITUTE OF JUSTICE. 
Rockville, Md. : NCJRS,Criminal justice, Administration of -- United States
-- Bibliography -- Databases. Crime -- United States -- Bibliography -- 
Databases. Criminals -- United States -- Bibliography -- Databases. 
<P>
<A NAME="Fic">
<H5>Fiction; Literature; Popular culture</H5>

P94 .P67 1994. POPULAR CULTURE [VIDEORECORDING] : RAGE, RIGHTS, AND 
RESPONSIBILITY / A PRODUCTION OF SOCRATIC SEMINARS IN ASSOCIATION WITH THE 
GRADUATE SCHOOL OF JOURNALISM, COLUMBIA UNIVERSITY AND WNET/NEW YORK ; 
EXECUTIVE PRODUCER, STUART F. SUCHERMAN ; PRODUCER, MARC MORGENSTERN ; 
DIRECTOR & BROADCAST PRODUCER, MARK GANGUZZA. [Alexandria, Va.] : PBS Video,
c1994. Popular culture -- United States. Mass media -- Influence. Mass 
media -- Social aspects -- United States. Freedom and art -- United States.
<P>
PE1072 .B76 1990. Bryson, Bill. THE MOTHER TONGUE : ENGLISH & HOW IT GOT 
THAT WAY / BILL BRYSON. New York : W. Morrow, c1990. English language -- 
History. 
<P>
PN4193.I5 S56 1991. Simmons, S. H. (Sylvia H.). HOW TO BE THE LIFE OF THE 
PODIUM : OPENERS, CLOSERS & EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN TO KEEP THEM LISTENING / 
SYLVIA SIMMONS. New York, NY : AMACOM, c1991. Public speaking -- Handbooks,
manuals, etc. Wit and humor. 

<P>

PR2007.K4 L72 1983. Collis, Louise. MEMOIRS OF A MEDIEVAL WOMAN : THE LIFE 
AND TIMES OF MARGERY KEMPE / LOUISE COLLIS. New York, N.Y. : Harper 
Colophon Books, 1983. Kempe, Margery, b. ca. 1373. Authors, English -- 
Middle English, 1100-1500 -- Biography. 
<P>
PR2807 .T75 1996. TRIAL OF HAMLET [VIDEORECORDING] / BOSTON BAR ASSOCIATION
& HUNTINGTON THEATRE COMPANY ; C-SPAN. [West Lafayette, Ind.] : Purdue 
University Public Affairs Video Archives, c1996. Shakespeare, William, 1564
-1616. Hamlet. Guilt (Law) in literature. Shakespeare, William, 1564-1616 -
- Characters -- Hamlet. Mental illness in literature. Shakespeare, William,
1564-1616 -- Characters -- Mentally ill. Mock trials. 
