<TITLE>New England School of Law: Native American - Indian Law</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">



<CENTER>

<H1>New England School of Law</H1>

<H2>Native American Law</H2>

</CENTER>

<A NAME="top">

<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<TABLE border= 1 CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=7 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="CENTER">
<TR><TD><A HREF="#primary">Primary Material</A></TD><TD><A HREF="#biblios">Bibliographies</A></TD><TD><A HREF="#collections">Collections of  Resources</A></TD> <TD><A HREF="#organizations">Organizations</A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=2><A HREF="#nations">Individual Indian Nations</A></TD><TD COLSPAN=2><A HREF="#aboriginal">Other Aboriginal Sites</A></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<A NAME="primary"><H2>Primary Material</H2></A>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/43/1601.html">Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act</A> - Cornell
<LI><A HREF="http://one-web.org/oneida/treaties.html">Treaties Project</A> - Oneida Indian Nation 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu:80/uscode/25/">U.S. Code, Title 25 - Indians</A> - Cornell Law School
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/25/461.html">Indian Reorganization Act </A>- Cornell
<LI><A HREF="http://www.halcyon.com/FWDP/resolutions.html">Tribal and Inter-Tribal Resolutions and Papers</A> - Center for World Indigenous Studies<BR>Includes documents from the Affiliated Tribes of Northwest Indians, and the  National Congress of American Indians (among others)

</UL>
<A NAME="biblios"><H2>Bibliographies</H2>
</A><UL><LI> <A HREF="http://www.mip.berkeley.edu/cilc/bibs/annotated.html">Annotated Bibliography for basic library collection of materials on
California Indians</A> - Berkeley 
<LI><A HREF="http://ublib.buffalo.edu/libraries/units/law/handouts/indian.html">Bibliographies on Federal Indian Law</A>  - U. of Buffalo
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tlt.com/conectn/na.htm">Native American Studies Bibliography</A>
</UL>


<A NAME="collections"><H2>Collections of Resources</H2>

</A><UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://fox.nstn.ca/~nstn1439/abolaw.html">Canadian Aboriginal Law
</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://indy4.fdl.cc.mn.us/~isk/canada/canada.html">CANADIAN FIRST NATIONS: Native and Inuit InterNet Resources</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://tamora.cs.umass.edu/info/envirotext/datadesc.html">EnviroText Data Descriptions </A>- Collection of materials which include over 2500 Treaties, Tribal Law Codes, and Tribal Contacts
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hg.org/native.html">Guide to Native People's Law</A> - Hieros Gamos
<LI><A HREF="http://kuhttp.cc.ukans.edu/~marc/geography/northam/federal_recognize.html">List of Federally Recognized Indian Nations</A> - U. of Kansas
<LI><A HREF="http://minerva.cis.yale.edu/~lisamc/native_env.html">Native Americans and the Environment</A> - Yale University, School of Forestry and Environmental Studies
<LI><A HREF="http://free.websight.com/Indlaw/">Native American Bar Association's Gateway to Indian Law Sites
</A><LI><A HREF="http://web.maxwell.syr.edu/nativeweb/subject/subject.html">Native Web page</A> - subject categories, includes some legal

<LI><A HREF="http://www.codetalk.fed.us/">Codetalk</A> - Information from Federal Agencies, part of the "superhighway through Indian Country" aimed at Native Americans
<LI><A HREF="http://www.fdl.cc.mn.us/natnet/">NativeNet</A>  - links to mailing list archives and documents regarding Indians re struggles, disputes, protests and ongoing issues
<LI><A HREF="http://bioc09.uthscsa.edu/natnet/archive/nl/">Native - L </A>mailing list archives

<LI> <A HREF="http://www.csulb.edu/gc/libarts/am-indian/index.html">The American Indian Studies Program</A>  -  California State University 

<LI><A HREF="http://neal.ctstateu.edu/history/world_history/links03.html"> Native American Electronic Text Resources on the Internet </A> -  links to electronic texts related to Native Americans

<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.uoknor.edu/indian/aihist.html">Amerian Indian Historical Pages</A> - U. of Oklahoma Law Center 
<LI><A HREF="http://lark.cc.ukans.edu/~kulaw/tribalaw.html">Tribal Law and Government Center</A> - U. of Kansas Law School program

</UL>

<A NAME="organizations"><H2>Organizations</H2>
</A><UL><LI><A HREF="http://www2.dgsys.com/~niga/">American Indian Gambling and Casino Information Center </A>- National Indian Gaming Association
<LI><A HREF="http://free.websight.com/10/">NABANet</A>: The Native American Bar
            Association Network Website
<LI><A HREF="http://www.si.edu/nmai/nav.htm">National Museum of the American Indian</A> - Smithsonian Institution
</UL>

<A NAME="nations"><H2>Indian Nations Pages</H2>
</A><I>Please note that some of these links are not from official tribal sources;  as is true throughout the Internet, the researcher must evaluate each source individually</I>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.charweb.org/neighbors/na/cherokee.htm">Cherokee</A> - Eastern Band of the Cherokee
<LI><A HREF="http://www.uark.edu/depts/comminfo/UKB/welcome.html">Cherokee</A> -  United Keetoowah Band of Cherokee Indians
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mcn.net/~coyote/">Cheyenne</A> - Eagle Wing: Northern Cheyenne, maintained by tribal member
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pride-net.com/native_indians/chicora.html">Chicora Indian Tribe of South Carolina</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://allcatalogs.com/choctaw/newhistory1.html">Choctaw</A> - Mississippi Band of Choctaw Indians
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ucsc.edu/costano/index.html">Costanoan (Ohlone)
</A> - and other Indigenous Californians: History, Current Events, Contacts, Native American experience
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/ArcticCircle/CulturalViability/Cree/">Crees of Northern Qubec</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.infomagic.com/~abyte/hopi.html">Hopi Information Network</A> - includes dissertation abstracts on the Hopi
<LI><A HREF="http://www.multigrafix.com/aorhenche/huron.html">Huron-Wendat Nation of Quebec</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.web.net/~innu/">Innu Nation</A>
 - E. Quebec & Labrador
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lumbee-tribe.org/">Lumbee Tribe</A> - North Carolina; official home page
<LI><A HREF="http://slic.com/~mohawkna/home.html">Mohawk Nation Council of Chiefs</A>


<LI><A HREF="http://www.unm.edu/~shubinsk/mohican.html">Mohican Nation, Stockbridge-Munsee Band
</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://crystal.ncc.cc.nm.us/NN/nn.html">Navajo Nation
</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.primenet.com/~sdn/">Navajo/Dine: Sovereign Dineh Nation</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.uslink.net/~lapratt/sandy_lake_band/">Ojibwe: Sandy Lake Band 
</A> - includes treaties, history of federal recognition
<LI><A HREF="http://www.paramount.com/ILore.html">Onondaga: The Indian in the Cupboard site</A> Information about the Onandaga by a tribal member who advised the movie makers 
<LI><A HREF="http://one-web.org/oneida/">Oneida Indian Nation</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://thecity.sfsu.edu/~mandell/plpt.html">Paiute Tribe, Pyramid Lake </A> - Nevada Reservation

<LI><A HREF="http://hanksville.phast.umass.edu/defs/independent/PCC/PCC.html">Pueblo Cultural Center</A> - links to the various pueblos of New Mexico

<LI><A HREF="http://www.gate.net/~semtribe/">Seminole Tribe of Florida
</A><LI><A HREF="http://www.state.sd.us/state/executive/tourism/sioux/sioux.htm">Sioux Nation</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://swcc.cc.sd.us/homepage.htm">Sisseton Wahpeton Sioux Tribe
</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.Lakhota.com/">Sioux Heritage</A> - much information about the  Lakhota language
<LI> <A HREF="http://user2.ucinet.com/~umatribe/">Umatilla Indian Reservation</A> - Confederated Tribes
</UL>


<A NAME="aboriginal"><H2>Other Aboriginal Sites</H2>
</A><UL>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.halcyon.com/FWDP/fwdp.html">Fourth World Documentation Project </A>- Center For World Indigenous Studies<BR>Valuable collection of documents from sources world wide.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.first-nations.com/links01.html">Global Aboriginal links
</A></UL>



