<HR NOSHADE>

<CENTER><H1>Comparative and Foreign Law</H1></CENTER>

<A NAME="country">

<H3>Links to Information about Specific Countries or Regions</H3>
<H4>Constitutions</H4>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.urich.edu/~jpjones/confinder/">Constitution Finder</A> - from U. of Richmond, T.C. Williams School of Law
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/law/index.html">International Constitutions</A>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://wiretap.spies.com/Gov/World/">Links to a number of constitutions around the world </A> 
</UL>
<H4>Collections of Links to Law-Related Resources from other Nations</H4>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.austlii.edu.au/">Australian Legal Information Institute</A>- Australian Federal and State materials
<LI><A HREF="http://www.siu.edu/offices/lawlib/chinalaw/">Chinese Legal Research Center</A> - links to Chinese (Mainland China, Taiwan and Hong Kong) legal resources on the Internet, legal
research guides and other information related to Chinese legal research. 
<LI> <A HREF="http://dosfan.lib.uic.edu/"> Department of State Foreign Affairs Network (DOSFAN)</A> - with links to the DOS gopher 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ilrg.com/nation_ref.html">Legal Resources by Nation (International Index)</A> - from the Internet Legal Resource Guide

<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.osaka-u.ac.jp/legal-info/worldlst.html">The World List</A> - Non-U.S. Law-Related Resources - by country

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/govoline/govoline.htm">United Kingdom</A> - U.K. Government Online
<LI><A HREF="http://www.abanet.org/home.html">Japanese Law and Regulation Information</A> - ABA Network

</UL>

<A NAME="other">
<H3>Other Sites with Links to Comparative and Foreign Law Resources</H3>

<UL>


<LI><A HREF="http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/forint/forintmain.html">ForInt-Law</A> - Washburn University School of Law
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.indiana.edu/glsj/glsj.html">Indiana Journal of Global Legal Studies</A> - Indiana University School of Law
<LI><A HREF="http://law.wuacc.edu/fcil/newsl.html">FCIL (Foreign, Comparative, and International Law) Newsletter</A> - Washburn University School of Law

<LI><A HREF="http://www.pitt.edu/~ian/ianres.html">WWW Virtual Library: International Affairs Resources</A> - Indiana University School of Law


</UL>


<A NAME="news">
<H3>International & World  News Sources</H3>

