<HEAD>
<TITLE>New England School of Law: Employment & Labor Law </TITLE>
<meta name="Author" content="David B. Wilson">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A NAME="top">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Employment and Labor Law  Resources</H2>
<HR NOSHADE>
<H3>Federal Sources</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF = http://stats.bls.gov/blshome.html>Bureau of Labor Statistics</A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dol.gov/">U. S. Department of Labor</A>
<LI><a href="http://law.house.gov/100.htm">U.S. House of Representatives Internet Law Library Employment, Labor, and Pension Law</a>
</UL>

<H3>Affirmative Action</H3>

<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.fga.com/aaaa/">AAAA</a> - American Association for Affirmative Action
<LI><a href="http://www.wco.com/~acasul/aa4.htm">History of Affirmative Action</a>
<LI><a href="http://essential.org/afj/mexam.html">Mexican American Legal Defense and Education Fund</a>
</UL>


<H3>Employee Benefits Law</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.benefitslink.com/">Benefits Link</A> - Internet link to information and services for employers sponsoring employee benefits plans
<LI><A HREF="http://www.benefitslink.com/erisa/index.html">ERISA</A> - Full Text, by Section
</UL>

<H3>Employment Discrimination</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/42/ch126.html">Americans With Disabilities Act</A></A> - 42 U.S.C. sec. 12101 et seq.  from Cornell 
	
<LI><A HREF="http://gopher.usdoj.gov/crt/ada/statute.html">Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990</A> - text of legislation
<LI><A HREF="http://janweb.icdi.wvu.edu/kinder/ ">Americans with Disability Act Document Center</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.usa.net/ada_infonet/quizbook/default.htm#top">ADA Quizbook</A> - Quiz your knowledge of the ADA

<LI><A HREF = http://www.law.cornell.edu/usc/42/21/overview.html#subchapter-vi>Equal Employment Opportunity Information</A> - Cornell University database<BR>
<LI><A HREF="http://gopher.usdoj.gov/crt/crt-home.html">Office of the Assistant Attorney General</A> - Civil Rights Division
</UL>


<H3>International Labor Issues:  Abolition</H3>
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.comsec.co.uk/comorg/assi.htm">Anti-Slavery Society International</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.channel1.com/~aasg/index.html">American Anti-Slavery Group</A> - Abolitionist group 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cc.columbia.edu/~slc11/">CASMAS</A> - Coalition Against Slavery In Mauritania And Sudan
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hrw.org/">Human Rights Watch</A> - Investigations of human rights abuses in some seventy countries around the world
<LI><a href="http://www.creative.net/~penet/FoundTraf.html">STV</a> - Foundation Against Trafficking in Women
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cs.uni.edu/~lado/slavery.html">Sudani Newsletter</A> - Modern slavery in the Sudan
<LI><A HREF="http://www.utne.com/lens/cs/15cssudan.html">Utne Community & Society</A> - Slavery makes a comeback in Sudan

</UL>


<H3>International Labor Issues:  Child Labor</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ilr.cornell.edu/library/e_archive/childlabor">By the Sweat and Toil of Children</A> - International Child Labor Study Office Report
<LI><A HREF="http://www.essential.org/clc/home.html">CLC</A> - Child Labor Coalition
<LI><a href="http://www.globalpassage.com/ecpat/">ECPAT</a> - End Child Prostitution in Asian Tourism
<LI><a href="http://www.goacom.com/news/robbery.html">The Great Indian Robbery</a> - The Indian Express
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hrw.org/">Human Rights Watch</A> - Investigations of human rights abuses in some seventy countries around the world
<LI><A HREF="http://www.reebok.com/humanrights">Reebok Human Rights Page</A> 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.digitalrag.com/mirror/iqbal/iqbal.html">Iqbal Masih</A> - 1995 Reebok Human Rights Youth in Action Award Winner
<LI><a href="http://www.wizard.net/~friends/">South Asian Coalition On Child Servitude</a> 
<LI><a href="http://iisd1.iisd.ca/youth/ysbk000.htm">Youth Source Book</a> - International Institute for Sustainable Development

</UL>


<H3>U.S. Labor  History</H3>
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.iisg.nl/ialinkuk.html">IALHI </a>-  Links to The International Association of Labour History Institutions
<LI><A HREF="http://www.globescope.com/lpa/laws.html">LPA</A> - Labor Policy Association Listing of U.S. Employment Laws
<LI><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/history/">U.S. Labor History Chronology</A>
</UL>


<H3>U.S. Sweatshop Reform</H3>
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.bsr.org/bsrfact.html">BSA</a> - Business for Social Responsibility
<LI><a href="http://www.dol.gov/dol/esa/public/nosweat/trends.htm">Fashion Trendsetters</a> - U.S. Department of Labor listing of retailers and manufacturers who have pledged to help eradicate sweatshops
<LI><a href="http://www.stw.ed.gov/RFI/nclc.htm">NCLC</a> - National Child Labor Committee
</UL>


<H3>Wage and Hour Issues</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://dol.gov/dol/asp/public/programs/handbook/flsa.htm">Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938</A>, as Amended - Department of Labor
<LI><A HREF="http://twcdirect.tec.state.tx.us/employer/childlbr.htm">Federal Child Labor Laws in Non-Farm Jobs</A> - Employment Standards Administration Fact Sheet No. ESA 91-3
</UL>

<H3>Workers' Compensation Resources</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.iaiabc.org/wcother.html">International Association of Industrial Accident Boards and Commissions</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dir.ca.gov/dir/Workers'_Compensation/DWC/dwc_home_page.html">California Division of Workers' Compensation</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/topics/workers_compensation.html">Federal Workers' Compensation</A> - Cornell Law School
<LI><A HREF="http://www.wcb.state.ny.us/">New York State Workers' Compensation Board</A> - includes links to N.Y. Laws and Courts of Appeals Decisions
</UL>

<H3>Workplace Safety</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.osha.gov/">OSHA</A>
</UL>

<H3>Other Organizations</H3>

<UL>
<LI><a href="httP://www.adr.org/">American Arbitration Association</a>
