<CENTER>
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2>Professional Responsibility and Legal Ethics</H2> </CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE><BR>

<div align=center>
<TABLE BORDER="2" Cellspacing="1" Cellpadding="5">
<TR>
<TD><A HREF=#prim>Primary Materials</A></TD>
<TD><A HREF=#res>Research Collections</A></TD>
<TD><A HREF=#spec>Specific Issues</A></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><center><A HREF=#jour>Journals</A></center></TD>
<TD><center><A HREF=#art>Articles, Speeches</center></A></TD>
<TD><A HREF=#dis>Discussion Lists</A></TD>
</TR>
<TD align=center Colspan=3><A HREF=#org>Organizations</A></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</div>

<A NAME=prim>
<h3>Primary Materials</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www2.law.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/foliocgi.exe/model?">ABA Model Rules of Professional Conduct</a> - Cornell Legal Information Institute
<li><a href="http://www.touchngo.com:80/lglcntr/usdc/conduct.htm">Code of Conduct for Judicial Employees</a> - Administrative Office of the United States Courts
<li><a href="http://www.paralegals.org/Development/modelcode.html">Model Code of Ethics and Professional Responsibility</a> - National Federation of Paralegal Associations, Inc.
<li><a href="http://www.adr.org/standard.html">Model Standards of Conduct for Mediators</a> - approved by American Arbitration Association and American Bar Association
</ul>

<A NAME=res>
<H3> Research Collections</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/topics/professional_responsibility.html">Cornell Legal Information Institute  </A> - Professional Responsibility Law Materials<br>
(includes California, D.C., Colorado, Florida (opinions only), Idaho, Kansas, Minnesota, Montana, New Jersey, New York,  South Carolina, and Texas)
<li><a href="http://www.legalethics.com/legal.htm">Legal Ethics Resources</a> from Legalethics.com <br> (includes Alaska, Florida (rules), Iowa, Kansas (code), Michigan, Mississippi, Vermont, Washington).
<li><a href="http://www.ljextra.com/practice/professionalresponsibility/prrel.html">Legal Ethics Related Resources</a> - from Law Journal Extra<br>(includes Illinois)
<li><a href="http://www.ljextra.com/practice/professionalresponsibility/prdec.html">Selected recent U.S. Sct. and U.S. Ct. App. cases</a> - from Law Journal Extra
<li><a href="http://www.ironclad.com/gen-ref.html#Gen-Ethics">Ethics and Jurisprudence</a> -Canadian legal ethics links
</UL>


<A NAME=spec>
<h3>Specific Issues</h3>
<h4>Attorney-Client Relationship</h4>
<ul><li><a href="http://www.fwlaw.com/legalethic.html">What Every Client Should Know About Legal Ethics</a> - Fairfield & Woods, PC
</a>
</ul>
<h4>Business Ethics</h4>
<UL>
<li><a href="http://condor.depaul.edu/ethics/ethb11.html">DePaul Institute for Business and Professional Ethics</a> - DePaul University, Chicago</UL>

<h4>Lawyer Advertising, generally</h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.wld.com/ldstate.htm">State-by-State Advertising Restrictions/Disclaimers</a> - West Legal Directory
</ul>
<h4>Reform of ethical practices</h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://webusers.anet-stl.com/%7Ehvmlr/hm_pg.html">Legal Ethics and Reform Home Page</a> - Non-lawyer author
</ul>

<h4>Use of the Internet in the Practice of Law (including advertising)</h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.legalethics.com">LegalEthics.Com</a> Integration of the Internet into all aspects of the practice of law
<li><a href="http://www.computerbar.org/netethics/abawill.htm">The Ethical Boundaries of Selling Legal Services in Cyberspace</a> - William E. Hornsby, Jr., Esq. 
<li><a href="http://www.computerbar.org/netethics">State Bar of Georgia, Computer Law Section, NetEthics Committee</a> - Internet Advertising and links to other legal ethics sites
<li><a href="http://www.law.vill.edu/vcilp/MacCrate/mcle.lanctot.htm">The Internet -- Hip or Hype? Legal Ethics on the Internet</a> - Professor Lanctot, Villanova Univ. School of Law 
</ul>

<A NAME=jour>
<h3>Journals</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.ll.georgetown.edu/lc/journals/ethics/ethical.html">The Georgetown Journal of Legal Ethics</a>
<li><a href="http://www.ljx.com/practice/professionalresponsibility/index.html">Professional Responsibility News</a> - from Law Journal Extra
</ul>


<A NAME=art>
<h3>Articles, Speeches, Conferences</h3>
<ul>
