<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A NAME="top">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Sexual Orientation and the Law</H2>
<HR NOSHADE>
<BR>

<center><A HREF="#issues">Legal Issues: Health, Immigration, Same Sex Marriages, Military</A> | <A HREF="#journals">  Journals </A> | <A HREF="#lists">E-mail Discussion Groups</A> | <A HREF="#orgs">Organizations</A></center>

<H3><A HREF="http://www.nesl.edu/outlaw.htm">Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, and Transgender Caucus</A> -  New England School of Law Student Organization</H3>

<H3>Legal Sources</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.labyrinth.net.au/~dba/">GayLawNet</A> - from Australia
<LI><a href="http://www.hrcusa.org/issues/">HRC Legal Issues </a> - Human Rights Campaign 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.qrd.org/qrd/www/usa/legal/lgln/">Lesbian/Gay Law Notes</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.qrd.org/qrd/www/legal/">QRD</A> - Queer Resources Directory Reference List
<LI><a href="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/grads/g/Mark.Gray/Sex_Laws.html">Sex Laws </a>
</UL>

<H3>Congressional Votes on Homosexual Issues</H3>
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.vote-smart.org/congress/votes/Senate/Senate_Votes_By_Issue_All.html#HomosexualIssues">Senate Votes</a>
<LI> <a href="http://www.vote-smart.org/congress/votes/House/House_Votes_By_Issue_All.html#HomosexualIssues">House Votes</a>
</UL>


<H3>Censorship</H3></A>

<UL>
<LI><a href="http://fileroom.aaup.uic.edu/FileRoom/documents/Gsex_gender.html">Grounds for Censorship</a> - based on sexual orientation 
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://fileroom.aaup.uic.edu/FileRoom/documents/Cases/91oneMagazine.html">One Magazine</a> - 1959 Supreme Court ruling 
<LI><a href="http://oyez.at.nwu.edu/cases/72-862/">Miller v. California</a>
</UL>

<LI><a href="http://arts.endow.gov/">NEA</a> - National Endowment For The Arts Homepage
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://fileroom.aaup.uic.edu/FileRoom/documents/Cases/338neafour.html">NEA Four</a>
<LI><a href="http://www.his.com/~cosmos/biddle.html">In Defense Of the Arts Endowment </a>- Livingston Biddle, former chairman of the NEA
<LI><a href="http://arts.endow.gov/Resource/Catalogue/Chronology.html">1965-1995</a>:  A Brief Chronology of Federal Involvement in the Arts
<LI><a href="http://www.vote-smart.org/congress/votes/House/0642party.html">HR 1977</a> - 104th Congress, House vote to reduce funding for the NEA
</UL>
<LI>Robert Mapplethorpe 
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://the-tech.mit.edu/V110/N31/mapple.31a.html">The Perfect Moment </a>- Review by Deborah A. Levinson
<LI><a href="http://www.rockhall.com/visit/bios/barrdenn.html">Dennis Barrie </a>- former director of The Contemporary Arts Center in Cincinnati
</UL>

</UL>


