<HEAD>
<TITLE>NESL:  Registration Procedure</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A NAME="top">
<CENTER>
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<IMG SRC="images/regis3.gif" ALT="Registration Procedure" WIDTH=475 HEIGHT=63>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>

<A NAME="dates">
<H3>Important Dates:</H3>

<TABLE BORDER>
<TR>
<TH>Date</TH>
<TH>Event</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>April 8-9, 1996</TD>	
<TD>Senior Clinic Registration.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>April 16-17, 1996</TD>
<TD>Non-Senior Clinic Registration.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>April 22, 1996</TD>
<TD>Last Day of Fall Registration.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>August 26, 1996</TD>
<TD>First Day of Fall Semester Classes.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>August 26-30, 1996</TD>
<TD>Add/Drop Period.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>August 30, 1996</TD>
<TD>Last Day to Add a Course or to Drop a Course.</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>
<P>

After reading through these materials, you should complete the registration form and submit it to the Registrar's Office by the spring registration deadline April 22, 1996.  If you fail to register by this date you will be subject to all applicable late registration fees and penalties.<P>

A student's registration will not be considered valid until the initial tuition payment has been made.  The deadline for this payment is August 9, 1996 for the Fall semester.  Any student who fails to make the necessary tuition payment by the specified deadlines shall not be considered a registered student and will be subject to both late registration fees and penalties as well as the late payment fees and penalties which apply.<P>

In the event that a course becomes over-subscribed, preference for admission into the course will be given to students in their final year of study.   With senior pre-registration, the courses overenrolled with seniors will be closed prior to non-seniors registration.  If spaces remain in the course after all seniors are included, remaining students who signed up for the course will be admitted by random lottery.  Please note that registration is <B>not</B> done on a first come, first served basis.  Priority is <B>not</B> given to students who submit their registration form early.  If a student is excluded from a course due to over-enrollment, he/she will be notified by mail and posted notice.  At that time they may adjust their schedules accordingly.  Any student excluded from a course will automatically be put on a waitlist for that particular course.  This will be done randomly as well.<P>

A course may be cancelled due to underenrollment.  In the event of a cancellation, the Registrar will notify all affected students.<P>

During the registration and add/drop periods, students should frequently check their student boxes located on the third floor and the faculty and registration bulletin boards for important notices.<P>

<A NAME="confirm">
<H3>Registration Confirmation (Revised 3/95):</H3>

After the close of the Add/Drop Period, August 30, 1996.  All students will be sent a copy of their final course schedule as confirmation of their final schedule.  Students must return a signed copy to the Registrar's Office no later than September 11, 1996.  Course registration will only be completed with the return of the schedule confirmation.<P>

<TABLE BORDER=1 CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=7>
<TR><TD><A HREF="index.htm"><IMG SRC="images/home.gif" HEIGHT="36" WIDTH="36" HSPACE="5">NESL Home Page</A> </TD>

<TD><A HREF="regis1.htm"><IMG SRC="images/tocbtn.gif" HEIGHT=36 WIDTH=36 
HSPACE=5>Table of Contents </TD>

<TD><A HREF="regis4.htm"><IMG SRC="images/rtbtn.gif" HEIGHT=36 WIDTH=36 
HSPACE=5>Page forward</TD><TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=3><A HREF="mailto:webmaster@nesl.edu"><IMG SRC="images/letter.gif" HEIGHT="36" WIDTH="36" VSPACE="5" HSPACE="5" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>Comments to: <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@nesl.edu">webmaster@nesl.edu</A></TD>
</TR>
