<A NAME="cred_hours">
<H3>Credit Hours Required for Graduation:</H3>

84 credits<P>

<A NAME="residency">
<H3>Residency Requirements:</H3>

<H4>Day Division:</H4>
Completion of 6 semesters of residency, 15 weeks each semester.  In order to satisfactorily complete a semester for the purposes of residency, a student must enroll in the minimum number of credit hours required by New England School of Law and receive at least 9 credit hours of passing grades per semester.<P>

<H4>Evening Division:</H4>
Completion of 8 semesters of residency, 15 weeks each semester.  In order to satisfactorily complete a semester for the purposes of residency, a student must enroll in the minimum number of credit hours required by New England School of Law and receive at least 8 credit hours of passing grades per semester.<P>

<H4>Special Part-Time Division:</H4>
Students must comply with the day or evening division residency requirement.  In many cases SPT students may have a combination of day and evening  residency.  All SPT students should meet with the Registrar or Assistant Dean regarding this requirement.<P>

<H4>All Divisions:</H4>
If a student is not enrolled in or fails to receive credit for the required number of hours specified above, the student may receive residence study credit only in the ratio that the hours enrolled in or in which credit was received, as the case may be, bear to the minimum specified.  Any student with questions about the residency should meet with the Registrar, or Assistant Dean regarding this requirement.<P>

<A NAME="deans">
<H3>Calculation of Dean's List:</H3>

The following are the eligibility requirements for the Dean's List.  Upperclass students may qualify for this honor.  Eligibility is calculated each semester:<P>

<TABLE BORDER>

<TR>
<TH>Division</TH>
<TH>Requirement</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Day</TD>
<TD>A grade point average of 3.0 or better for the semester, with a minimum of 10 graded credits.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Evening and Special Part-Time Program</TD>
<TD>A grade point average of 3.0 or better for the semester, with a minimum of 8 graded credits.</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>
<P>

<A NAME="nes">
<H3>Calculation of New England Scholar:</H3>

The following are the eligibility requirements for the New Scholar Award.  Eligibility is calculated at the end of each academic year.<P>

<TABLE BORDER>

<TR>
<TH>Division</TH>
<TH>Requirement</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Day</TD>
<TD>Top 10% of each class for the academic year (not cumulative). Each semester must include a minimum of 12 graded credits.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Evening</TD>
<TD>Top 10% of each class for the academic year (not cumulative). Each semester must include a minimum of 9 graded credits.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Special Part-Time and Transfer-In Students</TD>
<TD>Grade point average equal to the equivalent of top 10% of day or evening division for the academic year, depending on division in which most credits are taken. (not cumulative)<BR>
Each semester must include a minimum of 9 graded credits.</TD>		

</TABLE>

