<H5>Second Assignment: Hamilton 34 - 58</H5>
<PRE>
     Be prepared to discuss in class

          The present value of an annuity at 3%, 6%, and 12 %
               For a perpetual stream of income of $1000 per year
                    (See formula at page 35)
          The present value of an annuity at 3%, 6%, and 12 %
               For a stream of income of $1000 per year for 50 years
                    (See Table 2.3)
          Explain the difference between the two PV.

          "The higher the rate, the less a future payment is worth."
                    Explain.

          Which is the appropriate discount rate to use when you
               are planning your retirement?  (P.  37)
          What is the difference between saving $100/month beginning
               At age 25 and saving $200/month beginning at age 35,
               In roughly estimated terms?

          What is the rule of 72?

          In general, for household bills, is it preferable to use a checking account
               Or an ATM withdrawal and purchase of money orders?
                         Compare fees and float.

          Is a personal check a negotiable instrument?

          Examine float with ATMS, phone cards & traveler's checks, 
     money orders, Certified Checks, credit cards, debit cards, wire transfers

          What is federal deposit insurance?

          What does the federal reserve system have to do with clearing checks?

          What does the Expedited Funds Availability Act do?

          What is an overdraft?  A post-dated check?

          Why have private check-cashing firms grown into big business?

</PRE>

