<H4>III. More Mysteries of Federalism</H4>

<H4>Part One: Introduction to the Mysteries of Erie
     (When and why must federal courts apply state law?)
</H4>
<H5>Assignment for Monday, 9/16:</H5>
  
<UL>
<LI>
 <I> Read:  </I><BR>   Federal Rules p 836 (28 U.S.C. 1652 (Rules of
Decision Act));
          Marcus, Redish & Sherman pp 914-25 (including notes)

    <LI><I> Focus</I>: the Erie problem<BR>

    <LI><I> Supplemental Readings</I>: <BR>You might find helpful for this
     assignment:
         <UL>
