<HEAD>
<TITLE>NESL: Personal Income Tax 1 -- Professor Salter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A NAME = "top">
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2> PERSONAL  INCOME TAXATION  "A" - PROFESSOR SALTER</H2>
<H3>Class Notes - for August 29, 1996 </H3>
<H4>Fall, 1996</H4>

</CENTER>

<HR noshade>
<pre>
1.  Review exercise - Organize & go to next level of detail

   Tax Type:   Fed.Income| State Income| Soc.Sec| W/H  | Sales  | Property
                                                                    
 Concept                       
                                             
   Tax Base       IRC 61    usu. Federal   wages  wages  price    assessed
                exclusions   with adj.     to cap         of      value
                deductions                               item     of RE

   Tax Rate(s)    IRC 1;    varies        worker/ table  varies   varies
               exemptions   by state    employer;          by       by
                 IRC 151                self-emp          state   locality
                                                  
   Tax Unit    indiv. or     indiv. or  indiv.    payee   buyer   parcel
                 married       married
                  couple        couple

   Tax Period    year         year       year     payday  buyday  annual
                    (usu. cal.)  

   Tax Payer     person       person     worker &  payor  seller  owner
                 w/ control   w/control  employer    

   Incidence     taxpayer     taxpayer   worker    payee  buyer   occupant?
     ????                                (employer?)      seller? customer?
                                         (consumer?)      maker?  owner?


  Note:  Other taxes - e.g. customs duties, gasoline, estate & gift, highway
          terminology:  "broad-based" taxes;  user fees; earmarked taxes


2.  Time value of money  --  Compound Interest - valuing the lottery win
          Key tax strategy:        deferral of tax due date - tax period
          Related concept:         acceleration of deductions




3.  Lottery win --  tie to IRC  

  IRC 61  gross income:            exclusions; inclusions
  IRC 62  adjusted gross income:   netting deductions
  IRC 63  taxable income:          personal deductions
  IRC 151                          personal exemptions

</PRE>

