<HEAD>
<TITLE>NESL: Personal Income Tax 1 -- Professor Salter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><A NAME = "top">
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2> PERSONAL  INCOME TAXATION  "A" - PROFESSOR SALTER</H2>
<H3>Handout No.  4  -  Notes for September 3 </H3>
<H4>Fall, 1996</H4>

</CENTER>

<HR noshade>

<H5>Previous Handouts:</H5>

<OL>
<LI>     <A HREF="tax1.htm"> Course Information </A>
<LI>      <A HREF="tax2.htm">Schedule of Assignments</A>
<LI>      <A HREF="tax3.htm">Notes for August 29</A>
</OL>

<PRE>
Handout No.  4           Notes for September 3

1.  Today
     Review Recovery of Capital
          Inaja Land Company situation 
               Purchase - $61,000 Capital Invested
                    Sale of Part - Easement for $Net 49,000
               ISSUE: Is some part of the $49,000 Gross Receipt
                         EXCLUDED from GROSS INCOME
                         As a recovery of capital?  If so, how much?

               Alternatives:

                    Recovery up front (early deductions - taxpayer likes)
                    Recovery at the end (late deductions - more tax paid)
                    Recovery allocated over the holding period
                         By value of part sold, or other method
     Tie to the charts - Posin pages 72, xiii

          Review tax structure

2.        Relate to the annuity problem in Posin

3.        Relate to lottery winnings

4.         For Thursday - Assignment 3

</PRE>

