<CENTER>
<H1>Public International Law & Policy Group</H1>
<H2>Membership List</H2>

 <h3>DIRECTORS, FOUNDING MEMBERS, AND ADVISORY BOARD MEMBERS</h3>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<pre>                               
Directors:

Paul R. Williams        	Former Attorney-Advisor, U.S. Department
Executive Director       	of State, Office of the Legal Advisor for
		 	European and Canadian Affairs.  Currently 
			 a Fulbright Research Scholar,University
		                   of Cambridge.  

Michael P. Scharf        Former Attorney-Advisor, U.S. Department
Managing Director/       of State, Office of the Legal Advisor for
Secretary                Counter-terrorism, and for United Nations
                         Affairs.  Currently an Assistant Professor
                         of Law, New England School of Law.
                         

Mark Zaid                Public international law and international 
Managing Director/       criminal law specialist. 
Treasurer                

Founding Members:

Dave Anderson            Former law clerk to U.S. Supreme Court,
                         Justice Kennedy, and U.S.-Iranian Claims
                         Tribunal.  Currently an Associate
                         Attorney with Sherman and Sterling,
                         specializing in international trade. 
                         

Tony Arnold              Teaching Fellow, Stanford University Law
                         School, specializing in environmental
                         law and land use planning. As of August
                         1996, Assistant Professor of Law,
                         Chapman School of Law.  

Michael Byers            Former Legal Consultant to the Canadian
                         Ministry of Foreign Affairs.  Currently
                         Ph.d. Candidate, University of
                         Cambridge.  As of August, 1996, Fellow
                         of Jesus College, Oxford. 

Chris Cervenak           Former Attorney-Adviser, United States
                         Department of State, Office of the Legal
                         Adviser for United Nations Affairs. 
                         Former Attorney for the United Nations
                         Refugee Agency.  

Daniel Cole              Associate Professor of Law, Indiana
                         University, specializing in
                         international environmental law. 
                        

Chris Goebel             Former Fulbright scholar, Paris, France. 
                         Currently an Associate Attorney with
                         Curtis, Mallet-Prevost, Colt & Mosle,
                         specializing in international law. 
                         

Katherine Gorove         Former Professor of Law, University of
                         Mississippi.  Currently representing
                         Hungary before the International Court
                         of Justice concerning the Gabcikovo-Nagymaros 
			 Dispute. 

John Knox                Former Attorney-Adviser, United States
                         Department of State, Office of the Legal
                         Adviser for United Nations Affairs and
                         for Oceans, Environment, and Scientific
                         Affairs.  Currently an Associate with
                         and Austin Law firm specializing in
                         NAFTA work.  

Karin Krchnak            Former consultant to the Slovak Ministry
                         of the Environment.  Currently an
                         environmental law consultant.  

Marjon Kroes             Former legal consultant to the
                         Government of the Netherlands. 
                         Currently Ph.D. candidate, University of
                         Cambridge.  

Peter Lavelle            Fulbright Scholar, University of Warsaw,
                         specializing in east, East-Central
                         European political culture as it applies
                         to the transitions away from communism. 
                        

Greg Majio               Former consultant to the U.S.
                         Environmental Protection Agency. 
                         Currently Research Fellow, University of
                         Georgetown.  

Steve Stec               Regional Director for the American Bar
                         Association's Central and East European
                         Law Initiative.  


</pre>


