<HEAD>
<TITLE>Center for International Law & Policy at New England School of Law:  Bibliography </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A NAME="top">
<CENTER>
<H1>Center for International Law & Policy at New England School of Law</H1>

<H2>PUBLIC INTERNATIONAL LAW & POLICY GROUP</H2></CENTER>
<HR noshade>
<I>BOSTON, WASHINGTON, D.C. & LONDON
</I>
<CENTER><H3> MEMORANDUM AND PUBLICATIONS AVAILABLE FROM THE PUBLIC INTERNATIONAL LAW AND POLICY GROUP</H3>
</CENTER>

<H4>Memoranda</H4>
<PRE>
     Legal Memorandum: Whether the Continued Application of the
     United Nations Arms Embargo to the Independent and Sovereign
     State of Bosnia-Herzegovina Violates International Law.

     Legal Memorandum: The International Legal Status of a "Loose
     Union of the Muslim-Croat Federal and the Serb Regions of
     Bosnia-Herzegovina."

     Legal Memorandum: Whether the UN Mandate in Bosnia-Herzegovina Permits the Use of Force by UNPROFOR, NATO and
     UN Member States.

     Policy Memorandum:  General Assembly Action Necessary to End
     Application of the United Nations Yugoslavian Arms Embargo
     to the Sovereign and Independent State of Bosnia-Herzegovina.

     Draft General Assembly Resolution:  The Discontinuation of
     the Application of the Yugoslavian Arms Embargo to Bosnia-Herzegovina.

     Legal Memorandum:  What Options May the Republic of
     Macedonia Pursue in the United Nations to Assert its Right
     to Be Referred to as the "Republic of Macedonia"? 
     (confidential, available only to members).

     Reporting Memorandum: Observations Related to the Turkish
     Parliamentary Delegation Meeting with Lord Owen.
     (confidential, available only to members).
</PRE>
<H4>Commentary</H4>
<PRE>
     An Invisible Hand for Poland's Environmental, WALL STREET
     JOURNAL EUROPE, by Dan Cole.

     Time to End the Embargo, BOSNIA REPORT.

     The Arms Embargo as a Tool of Genocide, BOSNIA REPORT.

     The Crippling of Bosnia, THE TABLET; The Long Hard Slog to
     Bosnian Peace,  THE TABLET (response article by British
     Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd).

     Why the Bosnian Arms Embargo is Illegal, WALL STREET JOURNAL
     EUROPE, LE MONDE, by Paul Williams.
</PRE>
<H4>Research Articles</H4>


<H5>Environment</H5>
<PRE>

     An Outline History of Environmental Law and Administration
     in Poland.  HASTINGS JOURNAL OF INTERNATIONAL & COMPARATIVE
     LAW, by Dan Cole.


     Debt-Equity Conversions, Debt-for-Nature Swaps, and the
     Continuing World Debt Crises,  COLUMBIA JOURNAL OF
     TRANSNATIONAL LAW, by Dan Cole.

     Environmental Protection and Economic Growth: Lessons from
     Socialist Europe, in LAW AND ECONOMICS: NEW AND CRITICAL
     PERSPECTIVES, by Dan Cole

     Local Environmental Infrastructure Along the U.S.-Mexico
     Border: The Role of BECC and NADBANK, COMMERCIAL LAW UPDATE,
     by Tony Arnold.

     Marxism and the Failure of Environmental Protection in
     Eastern Europe and the USSR, in LEGAL STUDIES FORUM, by Dan
     Cole.

     Poland's Progress: Environmental Protection in a Period of
     Transition, JOURNAL OF EAST EUROPEAN LAW, by Dan Cole.

     Can International Legal Principles Promote the Resolution of
     Central and East European Transboundary Environmental
     Disputes?, GEORGETOWN INTERNATIONAL ENVIRONMENTAL LAW
     REVIEW, by Paul Williams.
</PRE>
<H5>Human Rights</H5>
<PRE>
     Population Transfer, Humanitarian Law, and the Use of Ground
     Force in U.N. Peacemaking: Bosnia and Herzegovina in the
     Wake of Iraq, NEW YORK JOURNAL OF INTERNATIONAL LAW AND
     POLITICS, by Christopher Goebel.

     Swapping Amnesty for Peace, TEXAS INTERNATIONAL LAW JOURNAL,
     by Michael Scharf.

     The Timing of Ethnic Conflict, by Peter Lavelle,
     (confidential, available only to members).
</PRE>
<H5>Former Yugoslavia</H5>
<PRE>
     The Legal Parameters of the UNPROFOR Mandate in the Former
     Yugoslavia, Chapter One of THE REPORT OF THE INDEPENDENT
     COMMISSION on UNPROFOR, by Paul Williams and Mike Scharf.

     Interpreting UN Sanctions: The Rulings and Role of the
     Yugoslavia Sanctions Committee, BROOKLYN journal of
     international law, by Mike Scharf and Joshua Dorsin.
</PRE>
<H5>States in Transition</H5>
<PRE>
     Bankruptcy in Russia: The Evolution of a Comprehensive
     Bankruptcy Code, Review of Central and East European Law, by
     Paul Wade and Paul Williams.

     Musical Chairs:  The Dissolution of States and Membership in
     the United Nations, CORNELL INTERNATIONAL LAW JOURNAL, by
     Mike Scharf.

     Treaty Succession: Conflicting State Practice, DENVER
     JOURNAL OF INTERNATIONAL LAW AND POLICY, by Paul Williams.
</PRE>
<H5>International Legal Theory</H5>
<PRE>

     Custom, Power, and the Power of Rules, MICHIGAN JOURNAL OF
     INTERNATIONAL LAW, by Michael Byers.
</PRE>

