<CENTER>
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2>Library Newsletter</H2>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
<H3>Notes From the Director</H3>

<I>Frank S. Bae</I><P>

In conjunction with the SBA, NESL has recently established a new program providing passes to the Museum of Fine Arts and the New England Aquarium to current students, faculty, trustees,  and staff.  The pass program is administered by the Library.  Passes are available for a 24 hour time period and may be reserved up to one week in advance.  Each Museum of Fine Arts pass admits 2 adults and all children 17 and under in a household.  Each New England Aquarium pass admits 4 people with a $1.00 admission fee/person.  If a pass is lost, there will be a $5.00 fee for replacement.  We hope you can take advantage of the opportunity to enjoy these cultural activities.<P>

Have an enjoyable and productive summer!<P>

