<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2>Library Newsletter</H2>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>

<H3>What's New in the CMC</H3>

<I>Chris Dugan</I><P>

If you've used the Computer and Media Center recently, you may have noticed some significant changes.  All of the old student-use DOS-only 286 PCs have been replaced with newer models.  Because of this, we were able to load Microsoft Windows onto every PC in the lab.  Also, we have added two new Macintosh Performas.<P>

Not only have we replaced our old HP DeskJet 500 printers with the newest models, but we've also networked the PCs.  This makes printing much faster and allows students to use the laser printer from any PC.<P>

There are also four new computers near the CMC that are equipped with CALI lessons and Telnet.  These computers also have Netscape Navigator on them.  By using this program, students can browse the World Wide Web, a part of the Internet that is capable of displaying graphics and doing other cool things.  Soon, NESL will be getting its own Web page that you'll be able to call up from home if you have Internet access.<P>

There are more changes to come.  Keep checking out the CMC to find out about them.<P>


