<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2>Library Newsletter</H2>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>

<H3>Favorite Web Pages</H3>

<I>Barry Stearns and Sandy Lamar</I><P>

The World Wide Web is an amazing resource.  Increasingly, it is becoming apparent that a library with WWW access can no longer say "sorry... we don't carry that."  A case in point: a student needed  O.J. Simpson's original mug shot and a copy of the doctored Time Magazine cover photo that appeared shortly after Simpson's arrest.  In the past the student would have been sent to the Boston Public Library because we only retain Time for four months in hard copy.  Well this time we turned to the Web and in a short period of time found and printed copies of both photographs.<P>

Take a look at some of the helpful sources, some fun, some serious, that library staff and faculty have reported as their favorites.  Happy Surfing!

<H3>Barry Stearns</H3>
<B>MapQuest:</B> <A HREF="http://www.mapquest.com/">http://www.mapquest.com/</A> This source is amazing.  You can request mile by mile trip directions simply by typing in the name of your departure and destination location.  You can also request detailed street level maps for any location in the country.<P>

<B>Switchboard:</B> <A HREF="http://www.switchboard.com/">http://www.switchboard.com/</A> Need a phone number anywhere in the country?  Try them and see if they have a listing.<P>

<H3>Sandy Lamar</H3>
<B>Pepper and Corazzini:</B> <A HREF="http://www.commlaw.com/">http://www.commlaw.com/</A> Information about communication, telecommunications, Internet and online services law.<P>

<B>Entertainment in Boston:</B> <A HREF="http://www.boston.com/globe/cal/">http://www.boston.com/globe/cal/</A> The Boston Globe's online Calendar magazine, with movie times, reviews, "cheap thrills" and more.  If you are too cheap to buy the Globe on Thursdays, this is the place for you.<P>

<B>LL Bean Park Search:</B> <A HREF="http://www.llbean.com/parksearch/">http://www.llbean.com/parksearch/</A> If you like to hike, camp out, or canoe, check this out.<P>

<H3>Helen Litwack</H3>
Native Americans and the Environment: <A HREF="http://pantheon.cis.yale.edu/~lisamc/native_env.html">http://pantheon.cis.yale.edu/~lisamc/native_env.html</A> This has links to 15 main subject areas and includes a 700-citation bibliography.<P>

<B>Mysterious Homepage:</B> <A HREF="http://users.aol.com/bchrcon97/mysteris.htm">http://users.aol.com/bchrcon97/mysteris.htm</A>
The page for mystery lovers, with links to discussion lists and Sherlock Holmes pages.<P>


<H3>Sarah Boling:</H3>
<B>I hate Windows:</B> <A HREF="http://florey.biosci.uq.oz.au/Windoze95Badge.html">http://florey.biosci.uq.oz.au/Windoze95Badge.html</A> One of hundreds of anti-Microsoft joke pages.<P>

<B>Funny Stuff:</B> <A HREF="http://www.leo.org/fun/funengl.html">http://www.leo.org/fun/funengl.html</A> For funny stuff in English and in German, if you would prefer, try this.<P>


<H3>Peggy Soo:</H3>

<B>BigEar:</B> <A HREF="http://barratry.law.cornell.edu:51231notify/buzz.html">http://barratry.law.cornell.edu:51231notify/buzz.html</A>  Lists sites referred to Cornell from Law-Lib., Tecknoids, and Lawyers' listserv.  It keeps me current and it makes for interesting reading.<P>

<H3>Anne Acton:</H3>
<B>Currency Converter:</B> <A HREF="http://bin.gnn.com/cgi-bin/gnn/currency/">http://bin.gnn.com/cgi-bin/gnn/currency/</A> This source is great if you travel or order from other countries.<P>


<B>The Shepard's Law Town:</B> <A HREF="http://www. shepards.com/ lawtown/homepage.htm">http://www. shepards.com/ lawtown/homepage.htm</A> I would recommend this as a way to get full text of current cases not available elsewhere (we had a patron wanting a first circuit case which was available here but not on the first circuit site through Emory).<P>

<H3>Eric Lustig:</H3>

<B>Our government at work:</B> <A HREF="http://www.irs.ustreas.gov/prod/cover.html">http://www.irs.ustreas.gov/prod/cover.html</A> Who would have thought the IRS had a sense of humor?  You can download tax forms, too.<P>

<B>Dilbert Zone:</B> <A HREF="http://www.unitedmedia.com/comics/dilbert/">http://www.unitedmedia.com/comics/dilbert/</A> He's all over the net, actually.<P> 


<B>David Letterman's Home Page:</B> <A HREF="http://cbs-tv.tiac.net:80/lateshow/lateshow.html"> http://cbs-tv.tiac.net:80/lateshow/lateshow.html</A> Featuring the top ten list.<P>

<H3>Jim Gage:</H3>

<B>Star Trek:</B> <A HREF="http://voyager.paramount.com/VoyagerIntro.html">http://voyager.paramount.com/VoyagerIntro.html</A>  If you are not a fan of Voyager, type as far as paramount.com and look for the link to Deep Space Nine.<P>

<H3>Ken Klein:</H3>
<B>Earthquakes:</B> <A HREF="http://scec.gps.caltech.edu/earthquakes/current.gif">http://scec.gps.caltech.edu/earthquakes/current.gif</A>  There's a whole lot of shaking going on in Southern California.  See this page.  (Sandy's note: earthquake surfing is encouraged at <A HREF="http://www.geophys.washington.edu/seismosurfing.html">http://www.geophys.washington.edu/seismosurfing.html</A>)

<H3>Charles Sorenson:</H3>

<B>Teddy:</B> <A HREF="http://teddy.law.cornell.edu:8090/questata.htm">http://teddy.law.cornell.edu:8090/questata.htm</A> No, not teddy bears.  This is Judicial Statistics. Data available includes information on 3.5 million federal district-court civil cases.<P>

<B>Federal Judicial Center:</B> <A HREF="http://www.fjc.gov/">http://www.fjc.gov/</A> The Center does research and also makes a lot of fascinating publications available.<P>

<H3>Tabor Wells:</H3>

<B>Wall of Shame:</B> <A HREF="http://www.milk.com/wall-o-shame/">http://www.milk.com/wall-o-shame/</A> From the author's description:  "This is my attempt to characterize the erosion of our world by displaying true stories and tidbits that are just too nonlinear."  It's amusing and true.<P>

<H3>Susan Tatelman:</H3>

<B>Business and the Law:</B> <A HREF="Http://www.rbvdnr.com/">http://www.rbvdnr.com/</A> 
 A law firm page with good links to Banking and Business resources on the web.<P>


<H3>Rick Roppolo:</H3>

<B>The Law Student Web:</B> <A HREF="http://darkwing.uoregon.edu/~ddunn/l_schl.htm">http://darkwing.uoregon.edu/~ddunn/l_schl.htm</A> A resource designed specifically for law students and those interested in the study of law.<P>


