<H1>New England School of Law</H1>
<H2>Library Newsletter</H2>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE><P>

<H3>NESL Internet Developments</H3>

<I>Sandy Lamar</I><P>

Watch for announcements about NESL's expansion onto the Internet. We are currently evaluating Web server software, and expect to be able to go public with our NESL home page within the next few months. If you have a commercial account with graphical capability, you will be able to access our home page and take advantage of the legal liks provided. In the meantime, if you are working on the NESL home page available in the library, and you notice we are missing a helpful legal source, please leave a note to <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@nesl.edu">webmaster@nesl.edu</A> and let us know of your suggested site.<P>

Plans are also in the works to establish electronic mail accounts for students, hopefully over the Summer term. We expect students to be able to dial into an email account that will be available to everyone with a communications package and a modem. This will make the Internet accessible at home even with an older computer and a slow modem.<P>


