<P><IMG SRC="cr_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 WIDTH=212></P>

<UL>
<P>Signposts to Government is the independent guide to information age
government, UK and international, published by <A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html">Kable</A>.</P>

<P>Signposts covers selected IS/IT policy developments and contract news
for government in a lively and accessible style, giving the insider's guide
to straws in the wind affecting electronic government, with commentary
written from the point-of-view of the citizen or taxpayer.</P>

<P>There are six main sections in Signposts to Government:</P>

<UL>
<LI><B>Newsbites:</B> news stories on what's going on in electronic government,
updated weekly.</LI>

<LI><B>Issues:</B> expert analysis of the most pressing aspects of government
IS policy, updated as developments unfold and including industry comments.</LI>

<LI><B>Projects:</B> factsheets on the most important public-sector IS
contracts.</LI>

<LI><B>Sitewatch:</B> a lively selection of the best and worst public-sector
related sites on the net.</LI>

<LI><B>Credits:</B> information on Kable's services and credits for the
Signposts site.</LI>

<LI><B>Contact:</B> messaging and e-mail facility for contacting Signposts
and Kable staff.</LI>
</UL>

<P>Sponsored by leading business solution providers:</P>
</UL>

