<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   <TITLE></TITLE>   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="">   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000"><img src="pu_line.gif">
<blockquote>
<H3>Immigration and Nationality Caseworking System</H3>

<P><B>Purpose:</B> To provide a caseworking system for the Home Offices Immigration and Nationality Department. The point of this is to be able to process applications for visas, asylum and passports quickly and efficiently and to be able to do background checks on applicants more easily. The contract involves computerising the department, to eliminate lengthy paperwork.</P>

<P><B>Contractor:</B> Siemens Nixdorf, under a seven-year private finance initiative contract awarded in March 1996 Siemens beat two other short-listed bidders, EDS & Digital and Andersen Consulting. </P>

<P><B>Progress:</B> So far the project appears to be on course. The contract will almost certainly involve job losses from the department but these are expected to be achieved by retirements and empty posts not needing to be filled. <BR>Due to the PFI nature of the contract Siemens will receive payment for services out of the savings achieved by the department which could be as much as 150m.</P>

<P>September 30, 1996 </P><pre></pre>&copy; <a href="../credits/fr.index.html">Kable</a> Ltd. 1996</BLOCKQUOTE>
</blockquote>
