<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   <TITLE></TITLE>   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="">   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000"><img src="pu_line.gif">
<blockquote>
<H3>RAF Logistics Information Technology Strategy</H3>

<P><B>Purpose:</B> To computerise the whole of the RAF, to speed up operational support and to save money. Overall the project is expected to save the RAF more than 1 billion over the next 10 years. </P>

<P><B>Contractor:</B> The LITS contract was awarded in 1995 to a consortium led by IBM along with Logica and Informix. The contract is worth 175 millon. </P>

<P><B>Progress:</B> IBM has decided to use BMC Software to provide the database and has also drafted in Robbins-Gioia to keep track of the development projects taking place. The system will work on several hundred servers with several thousand individual stations all over the country. The installation of this hardware is expected to take place over the next three years.</P>

<P>September 30, 1996 </P>
<pre></pre>&copy; <a href="../credits/fr.index.html">Kable</a> Ltd. 1996</BLOCKQUOTE>
