<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Central government UK</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/">
CCTA -Central Computer & Telecommunications Agency</A> One of the best official
 sites. Indexed, wide-ranging links to central government & other 
departments as well as local sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="minister.htm">Government departments</A> Quick direct 
links.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.Parliament.uk/">
British Parliament</A> Some useful information,  Hansard is now on the net 
but only accessible through a word search engine.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.coi.gov.uk/coi/">
Central office of Information Internet services</A>
Under construction - so offering disinformation at present.  If you like
press releases this is the site for you - worth keeping an eye on -
could get good.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.emap.com/cso/">
National Statistics - Information Gateway</A>
Fabulous statistic of the day - and links to statistic offices around
the world.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://dtiinfo1.dti.gov.uk/sfirms/">
DTI - Tendering for Government Contracts</A> 
Not just how to have your cake and eat it - but who made it, where it
came from and how to sue if you choke.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/charter/list.htm">
Citizen's Charter - Index of Charters</A>
Here they all are in full.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.keele.ac.uk/depts/po/table/brit/brit.htm">
UK Politics - Julian White's British Politics Page.</A>
Great links to UK government sites - promises to be checked weekly - 
includes all <A HREF=" http://www.keele.ac.uk/depts/po/table/brit/email.htm">MPs with e-mail addresses</A>.</LI>

</UL>

