<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Local Government UK</H3>

<P> This may look like a short list but every local authority on the net 

is accessible through the first two sites listed here.</P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.gold.net/users/fu30/localtxt.htm">
UK Local Government Web Sites</A>
 Clear well laid out site with links to all local authorities that
are on line with an option of a clickable map interface. Updated 
regularly and independently researched.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/">
CCTA Government Information service</A>
 Central Computer & Telecommunications Agency.
Well researched links to local (and central) government, discussion 
groups, right
through to "invitations to tender" - well worth repeated visits.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.tagish.co.uk/tagish/links/default.htm#health</A>
 Tagish - The Essential Directory of Information Sources in the UK
Clearly constructed site with masses of links to government sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.london-research.gov.uk/govlocl.htm">
Links to UK Local Government Sites</A>
London Research Centre, lots of links to local government, healthcare 
providers and UK universities.  Also hosts the UK National Inventory 
Project; a structured database on the hundreds of projects relating to 
information and society.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/David_J_Powell/">
Sites of London</A>  David Powell, a former London Research Centre employee, has compiled a full listing of the capital's local government sites, with additional links to libraries, and museums and lots of online guide books to London.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://lgcnet2.abasoft.co.uk/">
LGC Net (Local Government Chronicle)</A> 
Subscriber online news service giving up to date news stories on
government, parliament, Europe and local government.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.socitm.gov.uk">SOCITM</A> Society for IT 
Management 
- professional body - newly launched site (and a good start) hoping 
to put up lots more information. Links to local government and related 
sites.</LI>

</UL>
