<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Public-sector services UK</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nahat.net/">
National Association of Health Authorities and Trusts</A>
A one-stop shop for health information.  Check out the 'HyperGuide to
the Mental Health Act'.  How to commit a friend - mind blowing stuff.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.healthweb.co.uk/struct.htm">
Healthweb</A>
Information resource designed for patients and the general public.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.medwork.co.uk/db/index.htm">
medwork - NHS Organisation Listings</A>
Straight forward alphabetical listing of UK NHS services.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.healthindex.co.uk/nhsukg1.htm">
NHS and UK Government Sites</A>
Very simple site - department heading and description and away you go.
World Health Organisation listed here as well as Department of Health.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.healthindex.co.uk/cominf1.htm">
Computing/Infomatics</A>
List of IT companies supplying the Health sector.  With research
groups and more - mainly UK, some US.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ja.net/janet-sites/university.html">
UK Universities and Higher Education Colleges</A>
A - Z listing.  See <A HREF="academia.htm">Academia</A> for a variety of 

ways to access these links.
Very little available at schools level.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.tcp.co.uk/~chipster/">
John Hickman's Home Page</A>
Dedicated to all UK Police Officers with links to all the UK police 
sites.
Browse the United Kingdom Police & Forensic Web for connections all over
the world for police, forensic and related sites.  Fascinating.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.firenet.net/ukfire.htm">
UK Fire & Rescue Services</A>
Listing of all Fire Brigades (addresses & telephone numbers)
The Fire service seems quite badly served, compared with other
public-sector workers.</LI>

<LI><A 
HREF="http://www.fire-ems.net/commcenter/board/needinfo/messages/536.html

">
Fire & EMS Information Service</A>
Survey being conducted on performance figures on how quickly calls are 
answered.
For Fire professionals.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.uklegal.com/">
UK Legal home page</A>
Most useful for legal professionals but interesting material on the
Internet and the law.  Not quite as mind blowing as the US site (see <A 
HREF="psnonuk.htm">legal online</A>) but then we couldn't find one court 
facility in the UK that had got online.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.penlex.org.uk/">
The Penal Lexicon</A>
Best UK focused prison and penal affairs site.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ukindex.co.uk/nationaltrust/index.html">
The National Trust</A>
All the information on sites protected by the NT that you could 
possibly want.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.britcoun.org">
British Council</A>
 Set up to create partnerships between Britain and other countries - 
promoting
educational, cultural and technological co-operation.</LI>


<LI><A HREF="http://www.le.ac.uk./CWIS/AD/EC/RE/ecreps.html">
Public Sector Economics Research Centre (PSERC)</A>.  Run by Leicester
University - not a database but a full listing of the latest published
economic research on public sector funding issues.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.unison.org.uk/">
Unison</A> Web site of the largest public sector union.
Well run site with links to overseas public sector unions - with cheesy
piano accompaniment on the home page.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.keele.ac.uk/info/major.htm#general">
UK national services</A>
This site is still under construction but a good link site to public and
private sector technology partnerships as well as education & technology
research projects.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.poptel.org.uk/"> Poptel </A> Now an internet 
service provider originally established for the development of popular 
telematics. Subscribers include local, national and international 
The Fire service seems quite badly served, compared witorganisations from 
the labour movement, development agencies and 
single-issue campaigns and voluntary and community sectors (with links to 

their sites).</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ferret.co.uk/">Ferret Information Systems</A> 
Programs for calculating benefit entitlement (the world's first web 
benefits calculator), latest benefit news and a housing bill monitoring 
site. And links to sites on law and social welfare.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.oecd.org/puma/">PUMA</A> Public Management 
Service site deals with the OECD member countries and the SIGMA programme 

(public management issues in central & eastern European countries).</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.socitm.gov.uk">SOCITM</A> Societ for IT 
Management 
- professional body - newly launched site (and a good start) hoping 
to put up lots more information. Links to local government and related 
sites.</LI>
</UL>
