<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   
<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Public-sector: non-UK</H3>

<UL>

<LI><A HREF="http://world.localgov.org/">
The International local government home page</A> 
Select an area from a global map to gain access to community web pages
from around the world.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.europa.eu.int/">
Europa</A>
The Commission's home page with links to all member state government
sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.eea.dk">European Environment Agency</A>  
Comparing the state of the environment as this site sees it 
with the UK's own<A HREF="http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk"> 
environmental quango</A>. So many of the UK government sites are PR fluff 
- we really deserve better than this.</LI>.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.epos.nl/">
Interactive Network for Civic Authorities</A> 
Dutch inititiative with a great building interface. Members only - for 
people working within the public-sector and local government, around the 
world.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.soros.org/ilgps.html">
Institute for Local Government and Public Services</A> 
Forum for Eastern European governments funded by the (George) Soros
Foundation. Click on the swirl logo at the bottom of the page to see
what 'the man that broke the pound' is up to.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.nla.gov.au/oz/gov/federal.html">
Commonwealth Government Department & Agencies</A> 
The Australian's are really well organised on the net. A model of
access and democracy.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.nla.gov.au/oz/gov/">
Australian Governments' Entry Point</A> 
This links you to Australian state government sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.nla.gov.au/lis/govnii.html">
National Library of Australia</A> 
Government policy and the Information Superhighway.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.fedworld.gov/">
FedWorld Information Network</A> 
Another comprehensive round-up of government sites (mainly US) and
primarily a document ordering centre. These sites are really worth
visiting to see how information can be organised and how to keep up with
the flood of data.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.hotwired.com/wiredsource">Wired Source</A> - a new service from Wired Magazine - aiming to become the most powerful and succinct information resource on the net. Very US focused. Has  categories on US government and politics, giving online searchable access to the Congressional Record (US equivalent of Hansard) etc.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.prisons.com/">
Prisons.com  Moving Corrections into the 21st Century</A> 
The US penal resource site - very scary.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.legalonline.com/courts.htm">
legal.online - a guide to courts on the internet.</A> 
Complete round up of all courts, legal sites and law based networks in
the US.  As the site says, the Internet is not a substitute for the law
library yet - but as more and more courts make their decisions available
 it soon will be. At present, this site is a quick and inexpensive way of keeping 
up-to-date.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.un.org/">
United Nations home Page</A> 
Some very interesting stuff mixed with some bits that could challenge
the insomniac's home page.  Take a look at Databases - relief web - an
amazing daily updated site of places needing/receiving UN relief.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ustreas.gov/treasury/bureaus/finman.finman.html">
The Department of the Treasury Financial Management Service</A> 
This is the financial manager of the US Government - with everything from procurement
opportunities to debt collecting information.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.lib.umich.edu/libhome/Documents.center/index.html#doctop">
University of Michigan Document Center</A>
Incredible database of Government Web sites and related sites - US & Foreign also with the first link to the Holy See Vatican
Web Site (go to Foreign /Europe - Just below UK and above Wales! They are constructing a complete database of the documents of the Roman 
Catholic Church).</LI>

</UL>

<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 
<P>Signposts to Government &copy; <A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html">Kable 
</A>Ltd, 1996</P>
