<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   
<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Political Parties UK</H3>

<P>All the sites are very similar - but few 
MPs are net connected. To check if your MP will accept e-mail <A HREF=" http://www.keele.ac.uk/depts/po/table/brit/email.htm"><B>click here</B></A> Parties are listed in alphabetical order.</P>

<UL>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.unite.net/customers/alliance/">
Alliance Party of Northern Ireland/</A> 
Standard fare party site.
Facts and figures of Northen Ireland's election results since 1974.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="Http://www.conservative-party.org.uk/"> Conservative 
Party</A> 
Exactly what you'd expect with an 'Our Values' button - press the family button for 'Our Nation's Future' and a finger pointing button for 'People like You'.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.dup.org.uk/">
Democratic Ulster Unionists</A> 
Welcome to the DUP's home...All red, white and blue of course,
but not as in-your-face as one might expect.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.gn.apc.org/greenparty/">Green Party</A> Trying to 
show they're not just a single issue group but ready for 
government.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.poptel.org.uk/Labour-Party/">
Labour</A> 
Fairly bland with ordering facilities for rose earrings.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="libdems.org.uk/">
Liberal Democrats</A> 
About the best of the major parties' sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.raving-loony.pv.org/">Monster Raving Loony Party</A> Under reconstruction.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.u-net.com/~natlaw/">Natural Law Party</A> The yogic flying politicos.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.wales.com/political-party/plaid-cymru/englishindex.html">
Plaid Cymru</A> 
Plaid Cymru ar y We. Don't panic; the pages are a model of bilingualism - apart from the paper on devolution, which is available only Yn Saesneg.
All predictably earnest stuff.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.Referendum.org.uk/">
The Referendum Party</A> 
Britain's (or Mexico's?) Man of Destiny, Sir James Goldsmith, pitches his tent without
gimmicks. Includes a long essay by the host.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.junius.co.uk/">Revolutionary Communist Party
</A> Includes hot-links to Get the Met off the Net campaign. Right on.</LI>
 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.snp.org.uk/">Scottish Nationalists</A> 
No question about who is the enemy: the British Labour Party. Lots to 
read, lots of links.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.irlnet.com/sinfein/index.html">Sinn Fein</A> 
One of the best designed sites.  History of the IRA (impartial, of 
course) and the address for the Friends of Sinn Fein in Washington.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.users.dircon.co.uk/~thirdway/">
Thirdway Voice of the Radical Centre</A> 
UK political party campaigning for decentralisation of power through
constitutional reform.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.uup.org/">
Ulster Unionists</A> 
It's not Paisley's lot but the type size is really like being 
shouted at.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.btinternet.com/~ukip/ukiphp.htm">
UK Independence Party</A> 
UK out of EU party.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cnct.com/home/jbloch">The Scientific Selection of 
Political Candidates</A> "Lousy politicians result from the lousy 
selection of primary candidates".  How to introduce rigorous selection 
procedures as well as psychological evaluation to get the best candidate.  
Food for thought for all the above.</LI>
</UL>
<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 
<P>Signposts to Government &copy; <A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html">Kable 
</A>Ltd, 1996</P>
