<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   
<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Parliaments</H3>

<P>Most of these parliament sites are much the same.  Stuffy and
not very brave or adventurous in their approach.  Quite a few offer 
English pages - for the visitor.  The sites for Austraila, Canada, France and the 
US do provide texts of recent debates and bills - as one would expect; the test is how 
quickly the rest catch up and offer the this valuable resource.  Hungary and Romania offer 
a 'virtual tour' facility. The British Parliament is the most disappointing; one 
potentially interesting part was "factsheets" - intriguingly titled documents on 
procedural, historical matters (appallingly laid out) - but Netscape plugins have to be 
downloaded to read these "brief, informative documents" (unless you're 
running Netscape 3). Hansard is now online, but only accessible through 
a word search engine(access 'search the Parliamentary database' from the British Parliament site).</P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.Parliament.uk/">
British Parliament.</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.aph.gov.au/">
Australian Parliament</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.senado.gov.br/">
Brazilian Parliament</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.parl.gc.ca/english/index.html">
Canadian Parliament</A> - English option - with leatherette 
interface.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.assemblee-nat.fr/">
French National Assembly</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.senat.fr/">
French senate</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.bundestag.de/">
German Parliament</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.mkogy.hu/">
Hungarian Parliament </A>- with an English page and great tour.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.gov.sg/parliament/">
The Singapore Parliament</A> - in English, comprehensive services 
available.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://thomas.loc.gov/">
US Senate</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.loc.gov/">
US Library of Congress</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.althingi.is/">
Icelandic Parliament</A> - with some of the site in English</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.sejm.gov.pl/">
Polish Parliament</A></LI>

</UL>
<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 

<P>Signposts to Government &copy; <A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html">Kable 
</A>Ltd, 1996</P>
