<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   
<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Political Forums</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.keele.ac.uk/depts/po/table/brit/brit.htm">
UK Politics - Julian White's British Politics Page.</A>
Great links to UK government sites - promises to be checked weekly - 
includes
all MPs on the net.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.keele.ac.uk/depts/po/psr.htm">
Political Science Resources</A>
Huge site - links to everything political you could possibly want.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ifs.org.uk/disclaim.htm">
Institute of Fiscal Studies - Be you Own Chancellor!</A>
In conjunction with the BBC and ESRC - huge fun.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.herts.ac.uk/Library/inf/internet/language/pages/politics
.htm">UK Politics & Government</A> List of some of the UK parties - put together by Gwyneath Pearson - with a link to her home page.  This is what is so great about the net - individuals rounding up things that interest them and offering you a peak into their world.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.digiweb.com/igeldard/LA/">Libertarian 
Alliance</A> These people are dab hands at generating press coverage and debate - 
the libertarians have really found a home in cyberspace.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.gold.ac.uk/~cea01sig/">Sean Gabb </A> A libertarian site, acting like a small press publisher on those favourite issues - freedom, guns, pornography, drugs and tax avoidance with great links.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.mori.com/">
Mori</A> All the latest political polls and links to other research & 
survey companies.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.the2000foundation.org.uk/">
The Conservative 2000 Foundation</A>
The John Redwood Homepage, well he probably likes it.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cnct.com/home/jbloch">The Scientific Selection of 
Political Candidates</A> "Lousy politicians result from the lousy 
selection of primary candidates".  How to introduce rigorous selection 
procedures as well as psychological evaluation to get the best 
candidate.</LI>
</UL>
<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 
