<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN"><HTML><HEAD>   
<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Pressure groups / Think tanks</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/">
The Electronic Frontier Foundation</A>
One of the six most-linked to sites on the entire web - or so it says. A civil liberties organisation dedicated to free speech,
public access as well as responsibility in new media. The essential
guide to the key issues.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www1.ifs.org.uk/index.htm">
Institute of Fiscal Studies</A>
There aim is to publish all their work in some form on the web.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/oft/ofthome.htm">
Office of Fair Trading</A>
Government funded organisation - to protect consumer interests.  Well
laid out.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.tecc.co.uk/workers/workers.html">
UK Welfare at Work</A>
A resource for Trade Union activists.  Tuned into the protest against US
censorship laws for the net - and links to trade unions and political
parties.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.policy.com/">
Policy Street - Tap into the world of policy online</A>
Links with (mainly) US think tanks and discussion groups.  Read up on a
policy topic from the point of view of a think tank, business, advocacy, industry or 
government.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cyberpoint.co.uk/asi/">
Adam Smith Institute.</A>
Not a database - more a list of their publications. Site needs more
thought.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ippr.org.uk/">
Institute of Public Policy Research.</A>
A  think tank web site not wanting to give anything away.  Some
links but mainly snail mail addresses to like minded organisations.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cityscape.co.uk/users/fj22/index.html">
Demos</A> Left of centre think tank - mostly listing publications and not 
very up-to-date.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.gn.apc.org/charter88/online/index.html">
Charter 88</A>
Pressure group for the reform of our government system. There's a rolling

petition here and democratic digital links.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.unison.org.uk/">
Unison</A> Web site of the largest public sector union.
Well run site with links to overseas public sector unions - with cheesy
piano accompaniment on the home page.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.poptel.org.uk/greypages/">
Poptel's Grey Pages</A>
A listing (snail-mail mostly) and some e-mail sites of pressure groups,
public bodies and charities - under development but looks very
promising.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.foe.co.uk/">
Friends of the Earth</A>
Their main campaigns and links to local offices and other groups.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/dpr/dprhome.htm">
The Data Protection Registrar</A>
Using the law to protect your information.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.fedworld.gov/">
FedWorld Information Network</A>
Put together by The National Technical Information Service to round up
US Government online information.  Always good when interested but
non-affiliated groups list government resources.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.compulink.co.uk/~fedtrust/">
Federal Trust</A>
UK research Institute on European integration</LI>

</UL>
<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 
