<TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   <META NAME="GENERATOR" 
CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sd_line.gif" HEIGHT=39 
WIDTH=212></P><BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Signposts Directory</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Academia</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lib.umich.edu/libhome/Documents.center/index.html#doctop">
University of Michigan Document Center</A>
Incredible database of Government Web sites and related sites - US & Foreign also with the first link to the Holy See Vatican
Web Site (go to Foreign /Europe - Just below UK and above Wales! They are constructing a complete database of the documents of the Roman 
Catholic Church).</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ja.net/janet-sites/university.html">
UK Universities and Higher Education Colleges</A> 
A - Z listing</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.ac.uk/">
The Open University</A> 
This must be the university with the most to gain from the net.  With an
interesting section on studying via the internet.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.uea.ac.uk/menu/student_union/links/links.htm">
UK Student Unions</A> 
Listing of all sites.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.essex.ac.uk/government/index.html">
Government at Essex</A> 
Site for the Department of Government.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.uh.edu/www_resources/arlinks-gov.html">
University of Houston</A> Academic & Research - Government
Covering US government, law and congress issues - and outstanding database.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.le.ac.uk/cp/cp.html">
Scarman Centre for the Study of Public Order</A> 
Leicester University run site full information sevice & with useful links

to related sites - though appalling use of  colour makes quite hard 
reading.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.soton.ac.uk/~nukop/index.html">
New United Kingdom Official Publications On-line.</A> 
Researched and maintained by Southampton University. This is a database
of  government reports from July 95.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.le.ac.uk./CWIS/AD/EC/RE/ecreps.html">
Public Sector Economics Research Centre (PSERC)</A>.  Run by Leicester
University - not a database but a full listing of the latest published
economic research on public sector funding issues.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.deacons.cambs.sch.uk/univer/unilist.html">
Deacon's School, Peterborough</A> 
Clickable map of UK universities with an internet presence.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/~ncut/">University of Newcastle</A> 
Centre for urban technology research - an international focus for 
researching the links between cities and technological innovation.</LI>
</UL>

<P>Should your site be included here? <A HREF="mailto:kable@kable.co.uk">Mail</A> your details and we'll review it for the next update.</P> 

