<A HREF="fr.index.4.10.html">UK political party sites on the 
Web</A>.October 4, 1996</P><P>&quot;<A HREF="fr.index.30.9.html">5 of the 
Best</A>&quot; - our opening Sitewatch critique. September 30, 
1996</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P><HR WIDTH="75%"></P><P><FONT SIZE=-1>Sitewatch is 
a quick and merciless review of the best and worst public-sector sites on 
the Web.<BR>We judge a site by its :</FONT></P><UL><LI><FONT 
SIZE=-1>relevance </FONT></LI><LI><FONT SIZE=-1>information 
</FONT></LI><LI><FONT SIZE=-1>topicality </FONT></LI><LI><FONT 
SIZE=-1>legibility </FONT></LI><LI><FONT SIZE=-1>design 
</FONT></LI></UL><P><FONT SIZE=-1>Most of all, by whether it does the job 
it sets out to do. <BR>We plead guilty to subjectivity, and we might 
judge a site from a big Whitehall department more harshly than a small 
local council. <BR>Victims may appeal against their ranking, criticise 
our site, or volunteer for a slot as guest reviewer by emailing to: 
</FONT></P><CENTER><P><A 
HREF="mailto:signposts@kable.co.uk">signposts@kable.co.uk</A></P></CENTER
