<HTML><HEAD>   <TITLE>Signposts to Government</TITLE>   
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><IMG SRC="sw_line.gif" HEIGHT=33 WIDTH=206>
</P><BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Dinky Toys and Dumper Trucks </H3>
<P>Kable's selection of cute public-sector pages and those scary monstersites that are there to serve us all.</P>
<P><IMG SRC="dinky.gif" HEIGHT=51 WIDTH=104></P>
<UL><LI><A HREF="http://www.odci.gov/cia/">CIA</A> - Central Intelligence Agency:Teenage hackers recently changed the CIA's Home Page to the Central Stupidity Agency so the site is not accessible while they fix this little problem. When it comes back on line there are some great FAQs to make you chuckle.<B>Q</B>. &quot;Do the CIA de-stabilise South American governments?&quot;<B>A</B>. &quot;No, the CIA is a .....&quot; Yes, boys.</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.cs.sunysb.edu/~vislab/start_colonoscopy.html">3D Virtual Colonoscopy:</A> Enjoy a colonic journey down this 3D fly-through a site that is quite literally up its own ass. No cast list available - so fan mail to the Visible Human Project (see below).</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.bluemarble.net/~mitch/mongolia.html">Mongolia:</A>
This is a fantastic site. Opening with the option of a traditional Mongol greeting and going on to offer the constitution in classic Mongolian, this illustrates the beauty of the net. If what you have is information, your site can be interesting to anyone. If all you have is money - who cares- who is going to hang out on www.persil.com? We have gone through the mirror.</LI>
<P><LI>The <A HREF="http://www.magnet.mt/">Official Website of the Maltese Government:</A> Who's running the unauthorised version?</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.sevenoaks-UK.com/">Sevenoaks:</A> District Council'sVirtual Sevenoaks - cute as cute can be.</LI></UL>
<P><IMG SRC="dumper.gif" HEIGHT=41 WIDTH=136></P>
<UL><LI><A HREF="http://www.ukaea.org.uk/">The United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority:</A> 
The Decommissioning Home Page. Next time you have radioactive waste to get rid of, come and get the top tips from the nuke kids on the block. Mutate new friends easily on the net.</LI><P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/visible/visible_human.html">US National Library of Medicine The Visible Human Project:</A> This is under Dumper Truck 'cos if anyone out there is doubting what can be done on the net you should spend a few quiet moments here. The people working on this have created a complete anatomically detailed, 3D representation of a male and female body. Wow.</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.prisons.com/">Prisons.com:</A> Moving Corrections into the 21st Centuary No-one does it quite like the US. Clean, bright &amp; scary.</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.innotts.co.uk/~mick2me/verify.html">UK COPNET restrictedarea:</A> Freeze - nobody move - throw your mouse down and come quietly.Gulp.</LI>
<P><LI><A HREF="http://www.hyperguide.co.uk/mha/overview.htm">HyperGuide to the Mental Health Act:</A> The men in white coats are in cyberspace. </LI>
</UL>
<P>Researched and reviewd by Louise Burton</P>
<P>October 15, 1996</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P><HR WIDTH="75%"></P><BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Signposts to Government &copy; <A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html">Kable</A> Ltd, 1996</P>
