<html>

<head>
<title>What We Do</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><img src="images/what.gif" alt="What We Do" align=bottom width=267 height=67></p>
<h3><img src="images/people.gif" alt="People" align=absmiddle width=85 height=150></h3>
<p><strong>Understanding Customers&#146; Needs</strong></p>
<p>We can quickly and concisely summarise what we do with the simple statement:</p>
<p>&#145;EDS is committed to understanding customers&#146; needs and helping them to succeed.&#146;</p>
<p><strong>IT as a Tool</strong></p>
<p>At EDS we help our customers keep one step ahead of the game by analysing the broader organisational framework, beyond 
the current IT issues. We use technology as a means to an end. We see IT as a tool for addressing the key issues that stand 
between your operations and your objectives, a tool for creating opportunities for your organisation as you define them. We 
measure our success not in technological terms, but in commercial terms. </p>
<p><strong>Improving Entire Processes</strong></p>
<p>This may require better use of information technology or a re-evaluation of your entire administrative process.</p>
<p><strong>From Data to Information</strong></p>
<p>Every government department, local authority, support agency and even sub-committee has data. Some are overrun by the 
vast quantities of it. At EDS, we turn data into accessible and usable information.</p>
<h4>And Information to Action</h4>
<p>Then we turn information into knowledge and knowledge into action. It is only then the data becomes valuable.</p>
<h4>Adding Measurable Value</h4>
<p>Whatever methods of analysis are most suitable to your particular case, our goal is to add measurable value to your 
organisation, improving performance, saving costs, saving time, increasing both customer and employee satisfaction.</p>
<p><strong>Saving Total Costs</strong></p>
<p>Rather than aiming to save you a proportion of your IT costs, we identify ways you can save on your total costs. But far 
beyond cost savings, we improve business processes and performance. </p>
<hr>
<table width=480>
<tr><td width=25%><a href="pubsect.htm"><img src="images/ps_but.gif" alt="Public Sector" align=bottom border=0 width=102 height=33></a></td><td width=25%><a href="http://www.eds.com"><img src="images/worldbut.gif" alt="EDS Worldwide" align=bottom border=0 width=102 height=33></a></td><td width=25%><a href="who.htm"><img src="images/whobut.gif" alt="Who We Are" align=bottom border=0 width=102 height=33></a></td><td width=25%><a href="how.htm"><img src="images/howbut.gif" alt="How We Do It" align=bottom border=0 width=102 height=33></a></td></tr>
