<H4>Careless talk: daft things our mentors say about the Net.</H4>

<P>"The state did not create the Internet." John Major, October 1996.</BR>
"I don't think censorship should be banned." Quoted in Private Eye's "netballs" 1996.</BR>
"Microsoft is hard-core about the Internet."  Bill Gates, 1995</BR>
"The intellectual creations of individual nations become common property."  Karl Marx and Friedrich Engels, 1888.</BR></P>

<P>Can you do better? Send in your suggestions, preferably with a checkable reference. We'll post a selection of entries on Signposts to Government. Whoever submits the one that makes the editor laugh most will receive a signed copy of the brand new and highly acclaimed <I>Oxford Dictionary of Political Quotations</I>, edited by <B>Antony Jay</B>. Usual cereal-package competition rules apply, editor's decision is final, no cash alternative etc.</P>

<P>October 25, 1996</P>
<P>Signposts to Government &copy;<A HREF="../kable/fr.index.html"> Kable</A> Ltd, 1996</P>
