<html>

<head>
<title>Central Government background</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p align=left><a href="central.htm"><img src="images/cgovt.gif" alt="Central Government" align=bottom border=0 width=458 height=68></a></p>
<h3 align=left>&#160;<img src="images/bigben1.gif" alt="Big Ben" align=absmiddle width=150 height=288><strong>OUR BACKGROUND IN CENTRAL GOVERNMENT</strong></h3>
<p align=left>Over the past few years our successful partnerships with a variety of central government organisations and agencies has 
made us the market leader in the supply of technology and business service. </p>
<p align=left>Critical to this success has been our ability to participate in very aspect of the process from policy formation and 
implementation through to service delivery.</p>
<p align=left>This ability comes from the broad base of EDS skills, spanning management consultancy through systems development and 
integration, to and systems and process management.</p>
<p align=left>EDS consultants have worked with policy makers to increase the speed and efficiency of the policy making process, striking 
the right balance between value for money and effective service provision.</p>
<p align=left>We have a strong track record of translating policy concepts into reality. The combination of such techniques such as Rapid 
Application Development and deep corporate resources allows us to produce the right solutions to tight deadlines.</p>
<p align=left>In response to new procedures to administer internal and external markets for services and to determine where the best 
value for money can be obtained, EDS advises on the design and structure of accounting and financial processes. In the 
process, we can improve the quality and availability of management information.</p>
<p align=left>To meet the demand for continual improvement resulting from ever-increasing competition, we redesign business processes. 
We utilise economies of scale in the provision of computing and communication resources to deliver savings to our 
government clients. </p>
<p align=left>Among our achievements is the introduction of private finance to public service projects, creating innovative solutions to 
intractable business problems.</p>
<p align=left>People are the first asset of all government organisations. In a period of rapid change they face increasing personal 
challenges. They may be expected to change roles or even employer as our partnership adapts to new operational 
environments and new goals. Nobody has more experience in helping staff to meet these challenges. In fact, two-thirds of 
our UK staff have joined EDS as a result of a transfer of employment.</p>
<p align=left>In addition to supporting management and staff, we ensure that service is improved both in administrative procedures and at 
the point of delivery. The falling cost and greater availability of new technologies such as imaging, high speed 
communications, smart cards and others facilitates this process. </p>
<p align=left>We continually invest in emerging technologies to improve your performance. This enables use to evaluate the potential 
impact of technological as well as capturing its benefits.</p>
<p align=left>Equally important to effective deployment of new technology is the design and development of new working practices to get 
the most from the investment. At EDS, we ensure the two go hand in hand.</p>
<hr>
