<html>

<head>
<title>Our Services in Central Government</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p align=left><a href="central.htm"><img src="images/cgovt.gif" alt="Central Government" align=bottom border=0 width=458 height=68></a></p>
<h3 align=left>&#160;<img src="images/bigben1.gif" alt="Big Ben" align=absmiddle width=150 height=288><strong>OUR SERVICES</strong></h3>
<p align=left>EDS services to government cover the complete lifecycle of a project from identification of the critical issues through to management of your new systems and work 
processes.</p>
<p align=left>The Continuum of Services chart below shows our full lifecycle capabilities.</p>
<p align=left><img src="images/edsdiag.gif" alt="Lifecycle Capabilities Graphic" align=bottom width=400 height=208></p>
<p align=left>To describe these services in more detail, we can break them down into five main areas:</p>
<ul>
<li><p align=left>Consulting &#150; providing strategic business and technical advice to clients</p>
</li>
<li><p align=left>Systems Development &#150; both application and infrastructure software development</p>
</li>
<li><p align=left>System Integration &#150; the integration of computer and communications hardware and software to provide total solutions</p>
</li>
<li><p align=left>Systems Management &#150; all aspects of management from planning and provision through operational running to ongoing support of a client&#146;s computing 
environment and communications systems.</p>
</li>
<li><p align=left>Process Management &#150; undertaking business processes on behalf of the customer organisation to allow the customer to focus on its core business 
objectives.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
