<head>
<title>Local Government Background</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="local.htm"><img src="images/lgovt.gif" alt="Local Government" align=bottom border=0 width=415 height=66></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/mayor1.gif" alt="Mayor" align=absmiddle width=52 height=150><font size=4>OUR BACKGROUND IN LOCAL GOVER<strong>NMENT</strong></font></h3>
<p>EDS&#146; history in Local Government began in the early nineties with the contract to set up and run the Parking Committee for London on behalf of the London 
Boroughs. In May 1995 we were awarded the contract for the London Borough of Brent&#146;s Revenue and Benefits Service.</p>
<p>This contract remains the largest local government white collar outsourcing venture in the UK. Success at Brent was followed in January 1996 with the award by 
the London Borough of Wandsworth of a similar Revenues and Benefits contract.</p>
<p>In the London Borough of Brent, we have carried out a comprehensive Business Process Review (BPR) to identify where efficiencies could be achieved. The roll 
out of the recommended changes is now complete. The Revenues and Benefits processing is now conducted in a paperless environment. This system will be 
implemented in Wandsworth over the next few months after their Service Improvement Study has been completed. </p>
<p>EDS is committed to Local Government and its recent internal reorganisation created a division dedicated to this key strategic area. We have invested substantially 
in the development of an Image and Workflow system which will give increased efficiency leading to lower costs. With our investment in key technologies, we are 
able to accomplish significant cost savings without jeopardising the quality of service provision. <br>
</p>
