<html>

<head>
<title>Healthcare Our view</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="health.htm"><img src="images/healthtx.gif" alt="Healthcare" align=bottom border=0 width=245 height=66></a></p>
<p><img src="images/nurse.gif" alt="Nurse" align=absmiddle width=84 height=150><font size=4><strong>OUR VIEW OF THE SCENE</strong></font></p>
<p>Healthcare is Europe&#146;s largest public service sector in terms of both human and economic resources, employing 6 million 
workers and absorbing 6-9% of GDP. With countries throughout the world experiencing a demographic shift towards an 
older population and continuing advances in the quality of medical care, this cost is set to escalate. As a direct result, all 
healthcare service providers are under increasing pressure to control costs and improve efficiency whilst maintaining, and 
where possible, improving the quality of healthcare.</p>
<p>These pressures are causing governments to move away from publicly-operated healthcare systems towards a greater use of 
private service providers. This shift brings with it issues relating to quality management, equality of access to services and 
accurate planning for future demand. For the providers, economies of scale are leading to acquisitions, mergers and the 
creation of multi-service organisations.</p>
<p>In the pharmaceuticals industry, competitive pressures mean companies are striving to bring new products to market as 
quickly as possible. The development cycle for new drugs has shortened dramatically. The industry is serving a market 
whose needs are more complex and demanding than ever before.</p>
<p>Accompanying these changes are increasingly strict regulatory controls and codes of practice. There's a renewed focus by 
governing bodies on the benefits of allocating resources to preventative healthcare rather than treatment.</p>
<p>EDS estimates that last year the global healthcare industry spent over $80 billion on IT. This spend breaks down by region 
as Europe 29%, America as 50% and Asia Pacific as 21%. The industry has recognised that intelligent application of IT is 
one of the critical factors for the future success of service provision.</p>
<p>To meet the twin demands of increased quality of care and budget constraints, service providers are looking to implement 
IT-based solutions as quickly as possible. The main objective is to enable the rapid flow of critical information to and from 
all organisations providing care: GPs, specialist doctors, laboratories, hospitals and post operative care providers. </p>
<p>To achieve this speed and quality of communication requires a vehicle capable of integrating these sources. That vehicle is 
the electronic patient record. Such records, combined with an infrastructure linking all parties involved in the care process, 
enable significant advances in quality of care and cost reduction.</p>
<p>At the patient level, GPs and specialists can access an individual&#146;s medical and treatment history quickly and easily, 
thereby ensuring a correct and rapid response. Regionally, information extracted from these records can be used to monitor 
community health standards and plan for future demands on facilities and resources.</p>
<p>A key constraint on the implementation of new IT structures is the existence of legacy systems. Legacy systems are the 
existing computer and data storage systems that were not designed to be linked to other systems. Such systems make it very 
difficult to share and exchange information. Building new systems, while protecting existing investments and ensuring the 
existing systems continue to operate, is a major task facing the industry.</p>
<hr>
<ul>
<li><font color="#C0C0C0">Our View of the Scene</font></li>
<li><a href="hbckgrnd.htm"><font size=3>Our Background in Healthcare </font></a></li>
<li><a href="hservice.htm"><font size=3>Our Services</font></a></li>
<li><a href="hsuccess.htm"><font color="#000000"><font size=3>Success Stories</font></font></a></li>
</ul>
