<head>
<title>Background in Healthcare</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="health.htm"><img src="images/healthtx.gif" alt="Healthcare" align=bottom border=0 width=245 height=66></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/nurse.gif" alt="Nurse" align=absmiddle width=84 height=150>OUR BACKGROUND IN HEALTHCARE </h3>
<p>For over 30 years EDS has been providing information technology services to healthcare organisations. With 5,500 
healthcare professionals supporting more than 200 customers in 13 countries, we have established long term relationships 
that improve information capture, sharing and decision making. </p>
<p>Our experience in the Healthcare industry spans our corporate history and is the largest single contributor to our revenues 
world-wide We have approximately 290 health care customers, bringing in approximately &#163;560 million in revenue per year. 
Today our customers include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Insurers</li>
<li>Health maintenance organisations</li>
<li>Multi-hospital systems users</li>
<li>Medical and pharmaceutical suppliers</li>
<li>Physicians equity groups</li>
<li>Medicare</li>
<li>Regulatory authorities </li>
<li>Purchasing commissioners within Health Authorities</li>
<li>Variety of clinical providers</li>
</ul>
<p>In September 1995, EDS acquired Swift Information Technology from the South and West Regional Health Authority. This 
expanded our expertise in healthcare considerably and helped us to bring increased value to healthcare organisations in the 
UK. Combining the strengths of both organisations, we are now in a position to provide a comprehensive portfolio of 
information systems products and services designed to meet the needs of a wide range of healthcare organisations. </p>
<p>Our goals in healthcare throughout the UK and Europe are:</p>
<ul>
<li>To partner with organisations actively changing the manner in which healthcare is provided</li>
<li>To deliver information services which transform information into practical knowledge for authorities, providers, 
purchasers, suppliers and patients</li>
<li>To measure the value of our services by tangible outcomes such as improvement in quality, costs, ease of care, clinical 
pathways and disease management</li>
</ul>
<p>One technology area vital to achieving these goals is integrating legacy systems. Our experience on a wide range of 
healthcare projects has given us unsurpassed expertise in legacy systems.We have had unmatched success in integrating 
computer and data storage systems that were not designed to be linked to other systems. We have enabled very large 
customers with a mix of systems that have developed historically to share and exchange information. We build new systems 
while protecting existing investments and ensuring the existing system continues to operate without interruption.</p>
<hr>
