<head>
<title>Our View of the Defence Scene</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="defence.htm"><img src="images/defentx.gif" alt="Defence" align=bottom border=0 width=186 height=65></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/defence.gif" alt="Planes, tank and missile" align=absmiddle width=101 height=150><font size=4><strong>OUR VIEW OF THE SCENE</strong></font></h3>
<p><font size=3>Defence organisations are under constant pressure to provide improved capability with less resources. They must be more effective and more flexible while 
spending less. In this environment, implementing successful IT can make the difference in force availability and operational capability.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>In the pursuit of improved performance, the innovative use of IT is increasingly important. Whether enabling rapid response to unexpected situations world-wide, or 
applying new practices for business improvement, the application of IT and the management of change are critical.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>Today's missions require a more responsive, integrated operational capability. With joint operations on an international scale, greater emphasis than ever is placed 
on flexibility and rapid reaction. Defence forces are challenged to succeed with less equipment in a greater variety of situations and against increasingly sophisticated 
threats. Modern IT can play a critical part in optimising the availability and effectiveness of front line resources.</font></p>
<hr>
<ul>
<li><font color="#C0C0C0">Our View of the Scene</font></li>
<li><a href="dbckgrnd.htm"><font size=3>Our Background in Defence</font></a></li>
<li><a href="dservice.htm"><font size=3>Our Services</font></a></li>
<li><a href="dsuccess.htm"><font size=3>Success Stories</font></a></li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
