<html>

<head>
<title>Our Background in Defence</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="defence.htm"><img src="images/defentx.gif" alt="Defence" align=bottom border=0 width=186 height=65></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/defence.gif" alt="Planes, tank and missile" align=absmiddle width=101 height=150><font size=4><strong>OUR BACKGROUND IN DEFENCE</strong></font></h3>
<h4><font size=3>With Experience Comes Insight</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Through our broad range of services across a wide base of experience, EDS is meeting the needs of defence customers for information services and systems of 
high military worth. A prime contractor for both operational equipment and non-operational business and IT services, our experience uniquely spans research, 
operational and support functions.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>In order to contribute significantly towards achieving defence objectives, an understanding of the military environment is needed. With more than 25 years' in-depth 
involvement with defence organisations, we have great insight into the problems faced and the measures required to address them.</font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Benefits of Private Sector Involvement</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>The need for improved performance at less cost is shared both by defence organisations and the commercial world. Through expertise gained in the global IT 
market, we have been instrumental in applying commercial technology and best practice to military requirements, helping reduce risk and shorten development 
timescales. We seek to maximise the use of commercial off the shelf (COTS) products and minimise costs and implementation risks. Together with our leading skills 
in security technology, this allows us to rapidly develop solutions that have a profound and positive impact on the business of defence.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>Through-life costs in COTS-based IT are largely determined by package selection. Our vendor independence ensures selection of the right products from the best 
sources, as well as ensuring ease of technology upgrades and future enhancement. </font></p>
<p><font size=3>We have unrivalled experience of operating successful partnerships with customers, providing innovative solutions that contribute key resources and add value 
throughout the operations. We combine the customer's core business expertise with our industry focus, business and IT skills to deliver performance improvements.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>We also ensure that the essential supporting services and provided. These include:</font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>Security and safety assurance to establish confidence in critical applications</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Human factors to ensure that organisation, training, operator environments and ergonomics are optimised, and</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Full procurement support services.</font></li>
</ul>
<h4><font size=3>Take Advantage of IT</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>The expertise of EDS goes beyond IT to address the business of defence. We are functionally oriented into groups covering Operational Systems, Logistics and 
Research and Studies. Within each group we have people who share the experience and perspectives of the customers they serve, enhancing our ability to add 
value extending beyond the specification and implementation of new IT systems to the business challenges of process improvement and support.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>Toward this end we have developed a strategy which, we believe, distinguishes us from other companies in the defence market. Our key objectives are: </font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>To partner with organisations to jointly improve the methods in which military systems are provided<br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>To deliver IT services which transform information into practical knowledge for strategists, personnel and command in both operational and support 
functions<br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>To maximise the use of commercial products and minimise cost and implementation risk, and to ensure selection of the most appropriate components from 
the best sources, minimising customers' through-life costs<br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>To measure the value of EDS' services by tangible outcomes, such as improvements in quality, costs and timescales for development </font></li>
</ul>
<h3><font size=3>OPERATIONAL SYSTEMS</font></h3>
<p><font size=3>By integrating commercial products we can deliver cost effective systems which are reliable, easily upgraded and which are capable of inter-operating with current 
and future systems. To do this, we employ the highest level of advanced technical and large-scale project management skills.</font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Information Superiority</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Reduced budgets mean it is imperative to use scarce trained military staff to their best effect. Information technology can be used to automate methodical tasks in 
essential activities, giving key staff more accurate information and more time to concentrate on strategic priorities. EDS is delivering this ability to improve staff 
productivity in operations from command and control to ordnance disposal.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>With rapid expansion in the amount of data available and advances in commercial communications and IT, it is easy to be data rich while remaining 'information 
poor'. Defence forces are increasingly reliant on intelligent communications and support to turn the mass of available data into timely and accurate information.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>A leader in secure systems integration, EDS is delivering tactical and strategic IT which meets today's challenging needs whilst reducing the risks and timescales 
often associated with the production of new systems.</font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Joining Forces in Command</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Through affordable and reliable systems, EDS provides the IT support to make decision taking, decision dissemination and planning easier, faster and more 
accurate. Our versatile systems offer a platform to meet the demands of future joint and combined operations.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>With strengths in command and control, including mission planning and mobile communications, EDS is delivering advanced military information systems across 
land, sea and air. </font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Information is only Valuable if it's Communicated</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Flexible and portable communications systems capable of handling high volumes and rates of data, and operating in a variety of secure and adverse environments 
are essential. EDS is expert in the integration of rugged frequency management, messaging and secure communications systems.</font></p>
<h3><font size=3>LOGISTICS AND ADMINISTRATIVE IT</font></h3>
<p><font size=3>Logistics and support are key areas for efficiency improvements, allowing defence organisations to maximise operational effectiveness. The challenge is to deliver 
savings through new working practices while improving and not compromising front line capability and support.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>By concentrating on core activities, defence organisations can optimise the application of resources, ensuring that equipment procured is reliable and supportable at 
the minimum cost over its in-service life. Supporting activities, such as IT management, can be successfully outsourced to reduce operating costs, improve 
responsiveness and enable in-house staff to focus on the wider business issues which the information systems are to serve.</font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Making Sound Military Sense</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Using new technology and best practices, such as Integrated Logistics Support (ILS), EDS can help to reduce through-life costs and improve performance both in 
procurement of new platforms and in in-service support management.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>Effective information support requires a wide understanding of both technology and business issues, identifying what needs to be done and ensuring that it happens. 
As one of the world's largest systems integrators, EDS is expert in the complex process of bringing together diverse hardware, software and telecommunications 
and fusing them with business processes to create effective systems.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>This is further enhanced by our wholly-owned management consultancy, AT Kearney, which provides world-class consultancy skills to ensure that the benefits of 
IT are maximised and change embraced with minimal disruption and risk.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>In defence logistics, EDS has an unequalled breadth and depth of skill and experience, providing a range of services including modelling of requirements and their 
effect, systems development and integration and maintenance and post-design support. </font></p>
<p><font size=3>Whether for logistics, administration or infrastructure support, we offer IT that makes sound military sense. We believe that systems integration goes beyond 
technology, which is why we address business and human issues through process management and the strategic application of IT to deliver quantifiable 
improvements. </font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Best Practice for Business Benefit</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>Despite the unique needs of military organisations, many systems which are required to support non-operational defence activities closely reflect systems that are 
used in the private sector, particularly in the areas of logistics and supply chain management. The extent of EDS' commercial experience allows us to apply best 
practice in management, control and technology, which maximises the effective use of the customer's investment. </font></p>
<p><font size=3>EDS is singularly well placed to respond to the challenges of complex programmes, especially where change is critical to success. It is the only company currently 
working as a Prime Contractor on all three UK Services strategic logistics IT programmes. And the successful transfer into EDS of nearly 4,000 staff from the UK 
civil service demonstrates our proven ability in human resources management.</font></p>
<h3><font size=3>RESEARCH AND STUDIES</font></h3>
<h4><font size=3>The Link to Future Effectiveness</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>In order to maintain future operational capability within shrinking budgets, timely and focused research programmes are imperative. The fast pace of change in 
operational policy necessitates the adoption of a broader, more flexible approach. Future proofing is an inexact science but success can be significantly enhanced 
by directly linking studies to expected future military requirements and utilising powerful modelling systems to analyse the ever growing volume of available data.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>EDS has a specialist research and studies group focused on the long term needs of the armed forces. It facilitates strong links between the research programmes of 
today and the operational requirements of tomorrow, reducing the significant procurement risks associated with ensuring that future needs will be met cost 
effectively in long, high technology programmes.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>With leading edge capabilities in data, image and signal processing, including virtual reality, artificial intelligence and fractal processing, EDS has the breadth and 
depth to develop flexible individual solutions from a wealth of specialist skills. </font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Technology is only Effective when you Understand the Inputs</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>The ability to assess the effectiveness of weapon systems and platforms is crucial when defining and evaluating future requirements. EDS carries out a 
comprehensive range of work from strategic high level and feasibility studies to detailed operational analysis and technology demonstration. This draws on our 
renowned defence industry knowledge across land, sea, air and space to ensure a balanced, pragmatic approach to the use of technology. This understanding also 
helps us enhance the synergy between existing and future equipment.</font></p>
<h4><font size=3>Capitalising on New Opportunities</font></h4>
<p><font size=3>For defence organisations operating in newly commercialised environments, research and technology superiority provides competitive advantage. Spanning the 
global public sector and commercial markets, EDS can bring the best technologies and market opportunities to our customers.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>An understanding built up over many years in close relationships, such as our strategic alliance with the Defence Evaluation and Research Agency (DERA), mean 
that EDS can help address the enormous change happening in the marketplace and reduce the risk and timescales of exploiting opportunities for research and 
technology.</font></p>
<hr>
