<head>
<title>Our Defence Services</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="defence.htm"><img src="images/defentx.gif" alt="Defence" align=bottom border=0 width=186 height=65></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/defence.gif" alt="Planes, tank and missile" align=absmiddle width=101 height=150><font size=4><strong>OUR SERVICES</strong></font></h3>
<p><font size=3>EDS services to defence organisations cover the complete lifecycle of a project from identification of the critical issues through to management of your new systems 
and work processes. These can be provided as either as individual offerings or as an integrated service.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>The Continuum of Services chart below shows our full lifecycle capabilities.</font></p>
<p><font size=3><img src="images/edsdiag.gif" alt="Lifecycle Capabilities Graphic" align=bottom width=400 height=208></font></p>
<p><font size=3>To describe these services in more detail, we can break them down into five main areas:</font></p>
<ol>
<li><font size=3>Consulting &#150; providing strategic business and technical advice to clients. Our many technical assignments include sophisticated models and proof of concept 
demonstrators. <br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Systems Development &#150; both application and infrastructure software development <br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>System Integration &#150; the integration of computer and communications hardware and software to provide total solutions<br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Systems Management &#150; all aspects of management from planning and provision through operational running to ongoing support of a client's computing 
environment and communications systems. <br>
</font></li>
<li><font size=3>Process Management &#150; undertaking business processes on behalf of the customer organisation to allow the customer to focus on its core business 
objectives.</font></li>
</ol>
