<head>
<title>Wandsworth Borough Council</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="local.htm"><img src="images/lgovt.gif" alt="Local Government" align=bottom border=0 width=415 height=66></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/mayor1.gif" alt="Mayor" align=absmiddle width=52 height=150><font size=4>LONDON BOROUGH OF WANDSWORTH</font></h3>
<p>EDS has won a five-year contract to tackle some of the same problems for the London Borough of Wandworth that we recently solved for Brent. The outsourcing 
agreement covers Wandsworth&#146;s Revenues and Benefits services. The work will transform the job functions of about 150 staff.</p>
<p>Our responsibilities include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Revenue collection</li>
<li>Benefits payments</li>
<li>Customer service</li>
<li>Cashiers</li>
<li>Operation of the IT infrastructure</li>
</ul>
<p>In partnership with Wandsworth managers, we will undertake a Business Process Re-engineering (BPR) study to identify areas where workflow can be improved. 
The aim is to help Wandsworth Council reduce excessive paper through the intelligent applications of such technologies as document scanning and image 
processing. </p>
<p>The BPR will consist of a radical review of the existing business functions performed by all staff. By optimising the business processes, restructuring the organisation 
and supporting all changes with appropriate information technology, we will transform the full range of services.</p>
<p>Using such techniques has enabled other local government organisation to provide better customer service while reducing costs. It has also proved to decrease the 
number of repetitive tasks, giving staff greater job satisfaction</p>
<p>Based on the findings of the BPR, a wide range of recommendations will be submitted to management . Upon approval , changes will be implemented step-by-step 
over the course of the total project. This will ensure continuity of service and mastery of one set of work processes before implementing the next.&#160;</p>
<p><img src="images/wands.gif" alt="Wandsworth Logo" align=bottom width=283 height=44>&#160;</p>
