<html>

<head>
<title>UKCC</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="health.htm"><img src="images/healthtx.gif" alt="Healthcare" align=bottom border=0 width=245 height=66></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/nurse.gif" alt="Nurse" align=absmiddle width=84 height=150><font size=4>UNITED KINGDOM CENTRAL COUNCIL</font></h3>
<p><strong>LONG TERM RELATIONSHIPS THE KEY TO SUCCESS</strong></p>
<p><img src="images/ukcc.gif" alt="UKCC Logo" align=left hspace=0 width=136 height=176>The United Kingdom Central Council for Nurses, Midwives and Health Visitors (UKCC) is a self-funded regulatory body for all nursing, 
midwifery and health visiting practitioners in the UK. doctors who practice in the UK. The organisation is based in London and employs 
about 120 people.</p>
<p>We have worked with the UKCC through precursor organisations for over 15 years and since 1985 have provided a full facilities 
management service for the development, enhancement and ongoing support of their SPRINT register. </p>
<p>This database holds the details of all nurses, midwives and health visitors in the UK&#150; over 1.2 million individuals. Over 30 UKCC clerks 
keep the register constantly updated with qualification and fee-payment information as both public and private hospitals must confirm through 
the UKCC the eligibility of a nurse to practice prior to offering employment. </p>
<p>In 1991 we implemented a Local Area Network (LAN) providing a range of office automation services. The :LAN has been developed over the years to the point 
where it now supports the following services:</p>
<ul>
<li>Word-processing, spreadsheet, desk-top publishing and e-mail facilities for 80 staff</li>
<li>Links to the SPRINT mainframe system to download letters to practitioners for high quality laser printing</li>
<li>Bespoke client-server systems for:<ul>
<li>Professional Conduct</li>
<li>Contacts analysis</li>
<li>Mail lists</li>
<li>Overseas registrations</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>A system based upon the Peterborough Software PS2000 package to support the needs of their personnel department</li>
</ul>
<p>EDS also provides a full range of services to support the LAN environment, including hardware procurement and maintenance, application development, package 
evaluation and implementation, and full on-going support. The contract runs until 1999.</p>
