<h3><img src="images/nurse.gif" alt="Nurse" align=absmiddle width=84 height=150>GENERAL MEDICAL COUNCIL</h3>
<p><strong>ONE GOOD FRIENDSHIP LEADS TO ANOTHER</strong></p>
<p>The General Medical Council (GMC) is a self-funded regulatory body for all doctors who practice in the UK. The 
organisation is based in London and employs about 200 people.</p>
<p>EDS has recently signed a contract to provide a comprehensive helpdesk service to give front line support to all the GMC&#146;s 
systems. We will also be responsible for problem logging, tracking and escalation for all systems provided by other 
third-party suppliers.</p>
<p>As part of the agreement, EDS is assisting the GMC in developing a convergent IT to address evolving business needs. We 
also provide systems delivery capability to the GMC, and development work for a new system to log and track Fitness to 
Practice cases is underway.</p>
<p>The most rewarding aspect of winning this project is that the introduction to the GMC came from staff of the UKCC, with 
whom EDS has a successful relationship for many years. </p>
