<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>LISA</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="defence.htm"><img src="images/defentx.gif" alt="Defence" align=bottom border=0 width=186 height=65></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/defence.gif" alt="Planes, tank and missile" align=absmiddle width=101 height=150><strong>LOGISTICS INFORMATION SYSTEMS AGENCY (LISA)</strong></h3>
<p><strong>LISA: THE BRITISH ARMY&#146;S FAITHFUL ASSISTANT</strong></p>
<p>LISA is the first logistics information systems agency in defence. Its mission is to enhance the logistic effectiveness of the Army in peace and war by providing 
information systems, services and support. Formed in November 1994 the Agency has produced successful systems ranging from world-wide asset tracking 
applications to workshop management systems.</p>
<p>The Agency has a core of approximately 50 military staff who have current, first hand experience of military logistic operations in addition to an IT background. A 
further 250 civil servants, fully aligned with Quartermaster General&#146;s business ensure LISA maintains continuity of service to customers by understanding their 
business needs and developing prototype systems to meet them.</p>
<p><strong>A Performance Advantage</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership of LISA and EDS offers a uniquely customer focused information systems (IS) service to defence organisations, helping to reduce 
costs and improve performance in resource acquisition and management. Only the combination of LISA and EDS can provide instant, flexible and 
informed front line IS support to military logistics operations.</p>
<p>More than ever, budget conscious defence organisations must optimise the supply, management and maintenance of resources while ensuring that 
equipment is available and reliable at the minimum cost over its in-service life.</p>
<p>Offering specialist systems, services and support, we enable our customers to maximise logistic effectiveness, freeing them to concentrate on and 
achieve military goals.</p>
<p>The Partnership provides a faster, more effective and more comprehensive service, able to meet customers&#146; information needs through in-depth 
military logistic knowledge, front line experience, commercial best practice and global buying power. It emphasises customer focus, applying its 
skills to understand and work with customers to deliver reliable systems, quality service and ultimately business advantage&#151;to committed budgets 
and timescales.</p>
<p>Critically, the Partnership offers a highly responsive and cost-effective service, procuring millions of pounds of hardware, software and services 
through competition every year. It can free customers from the associated procurement cost, delay and effort and pass on the benefits of rapid 
delivery, economies of scale and volume discounts.</p>
<p>LISA selected EDS in rigorous competition and a variety of services can now be engaged through LISA.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Military Logistics and the Application of IS</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership has a balance of military and civil service staff who have a thorough understanding of all aspects of military logistics. Combined with 
a high level of IT skill, these staff are uniquely placed to advise on the best application of IS to the customer&#146;s business areas to ensure IT that 
works. With world-wide experience in setting up systems, from Rwanda to Bosnia, the Partnership can install and support data systems and 
communications in any operational environment.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Business and IT Consultancy</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership offers consultancy on the complete spectrum of information systems and support. This exploits best commercial practice in a wide 
range of business procedures, enabling customers to make continuous improvements to their capability and effectiveness.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Systems Development and Integration</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership&#146;s combined experience enables rapid specifications to be developed with confidence. The proven expertise of EDS as prime 
contractor on the Naval Logistics Information System UPKEEP, the RAF&#146;s Logistics Support System and the Allied Rapid Reaction Corps&#146; 
IARRCIS platform is available quickly and simply to LISA&#146;s customers via call-off contract. Experience of integrating diverse hardware and 
software allows the most effective products to be selected.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Operations Management and System Maintenance</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>From sites throughout the UK the Partnership offers a full range of IT services, from the operation and maintenance of customers&#146; IS to the 
provision of mainframe bureau and data services, enabling clients to concentrate on using and applying the information delivered.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Procurement and Catalogue Services</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership is experienced in identifying, evaluating and sourcing many hardware, software and systems packages and can procure components 
and supply items on our customers&#146; behalf, providing the benefits of economies of scale and access to the global IT market. Vendor independence 
ensures selection of the best service and discounts from the most cost effective source.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Project Management</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership provides project management and support staff, used to working in the military environment, and a range of skills and services 
including prime contractorship, quality assurance, risk management and project office support.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Network Services</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today there are few standalone systems. Providing the complete range of networking and communications services, the Partnership can manage all 
of the customer&#146;s data communications and networking needs.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Electronic Document Management</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Partnership&#146;s Document Processing Group has experience in all aspects of EDM, from requirements analysis and process design through 
workflow management to system specification, integration, installation and management.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Electronic Commerce</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Electronic Commerce offers the opportunity to further streamline the customer&#146;s business. The Partnership provides a comprehensive range of 
Electronic Commerce services including consultancy, implementation, and a managed service, offering significant strategic, operational and cost 
benefits.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
