<html>

<head>
<title>IARRCIS</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#808000" vlink="#800080" alink="#00FF00">
<p><a href="defence.htm"><img src="images/defentx.gif" alt="Defence" align=bottom border=0 width=186 height=65></a></p>
<h3><img src="images/defence.gif" alt="Planes, tank and missile" align=absmiddle width=101 height=150>RAPID REACTION CORPS INFORMATION SYSTEM &#150; IARRCIS</h3>
<p><strong>EDS REACTS RAPIDLY TO DYNAMIC SITUATION</strong></p>
<p>The EDS Interim ACE Rapid Reaction Corps Information System (IARRCIS) equips ARRC HQ with a rugged and versatile battlefield Command, Control and 
Communication information system, whether in-barracks, in the field or at the HQ of participating forces.</p>
<p>Utilising modern IT and communications systems, IARRCIS provides an integrated system which is flexible, yet secure and resilient and can be rapidly adapted and 
deployed in response to dynamic situations.</p>
<p>IARRCIS marks a new approach to defence procurement, for the first time combining commercial off the shelf (COTS) information technology with 
purpose-designed specialised elements to meet military requirements. Using rugged hardware, the basis of which is COTS, and software that is similarly available, 
IARRCIS offers more rapid development, reduced cost and reduced procurement risk, while improving overall effectiveness and interoperability.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Providing highly reliable and maintainable systems that are easily upgraded or extended and implemented with minimum risk, IARRCIS addresses 
the need for greater effectiveness and interoperability. Ease of deployment, use and support as well as a design which allows technology upgrade 
are key to EDS&#146; system.</p>
<p>IARRCIS provides secure fibre-optic Battlefield Local Area Networks (LANs), which interconnect secure, rugged PCs and provide users with 
productivity-enhancing software tools. Dispersed HQ locations based on LANs communicate over a Wide Area Network using X25 services 
(including Ptarmigan) and can be rapidly and widely deployed.</p>
<p>IARRCIS uses a commercial X400 message handling system to deliver messages across LAN and WAN, providing a cohesive Corps 
infrastructure. Support for standard military message text formats enables interoperability between IARRCIS and other systems and databases.</p>
<p>IARRCIS is designed to ensure effective message handling in a frequently changing, secure network. It may be used in-barracks with commercial 
equipment, thus providing a common operational and non-operational environment. Common software and communications interfaces seamlessly 
link peacetime locations and the field, providing users with sophisticated software packages and tools with which to prepare, distribute and receive 
information and directives.</p>
<p>The use of commercial products also offers reduced costs in training. The EDS developed management and user interface hides system detail 
providing an interface suitable for many potentially multi-national users.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
