<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Emergency Road Service</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="approvedautorepair.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaatravelagencies.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Emergency Road Service</h1></center>
<!-- This page created by SiteScript a proprietary tool of America Online Productions Inc.
Unauthorized use of this product outside of AOL is a violation of Copyright laws. -->
<H3>SUPERNUMBER(R)</H3>

<img align="right" width=144 height=96 src="membensupercard.gif">Finding help when you need emergency road
service in your hometown is as easy
as calling the local club number on your AAA membership card. But what do you
do when you need to make that same call on the road in another city, state or
province?<p>

The answer is as simple as 1-800-AAA-HELP (1-800-955-4TDD for the hearing
impaired). This toll-free SUPERNUMBER(R) allows AAA/CAA members who are
traveling outside their home club area to call for assistance 24 hours a day,
anywhere in the United States or Canada. Counselors are available day and night
to take your call and dispatch help as needed.<p>

AAA and SUPERNUMBER(R): We're always there.<p>







<center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="approvedautorepair.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaatravelagencies.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><hr></center><img align="left" width=75 height=56 src="aaalogosmall.gif"><h6>&#169; Unless otherwise specified, all content within the AAA Online site is the property of the American Automobile Association, which reserves all copyrights. Copyright AAA 1996. This page was last updated on Monday, November 25, 1996 at 9:33 PM. The webmaster for this site is <a href="mailto:webmaster@aaa.com">webmaster@aaa.com</a>. </h6>
