<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>World Explorer Cruises</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="windstarcruises.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="showyourcardampsavereg.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>World Explorer Cruises</h1></center>
<H3>Members Only Vacation Values:</H3>
<img align="right" width=165 height=218 src="worldexpphoto1.gif" alt="worldexpphoto1.gif">

Take advantage of the exciting travel opportunities and discounts that come with your AAA membership.<p>

As a member, you can receive a 15% AAA discount off brochure rates on all World Explorer Cruise sailing dates --  a savings of up to $509 per person!<p>

AAA prices for World Explorer Cruises' 7- and 14- day Alaska cruises are Alaska's best "per diem value."  Free third and fourth berths also are available when payment is made with a VISA card.<p>

<H3>About World Explorer Cruises:</H3>
<img align="left" width=250 height=161 src="worldexpphoto2.gif" alt="worldexpphoto2.gif">

World Explorer prides itself in being the uncommon route to Alaska.  World Explorer Cruises' guests are invited to participate rather than just spectate.  There is more time on shore to discover the great land of Alaska. Cultural and educational shipboard programs include such things as a lecture series on Alaska's history, geography, wildlife, art and culture; and over 40 excursions to choose from.<p>

The ship, the <I>S.S. Universe</I>, departs Vancouver, British Columbia, on  7- and 14-day Alaska cruises, from mid-July through August. All 14-day voyages sail the Inland Passage of British Columbia and the Inside Passage of Alaska, across the Gulf to Seward, visiting nine ports of call.<p>

For additional information on this special travel value, contact your local <a href="aaaoffices.html">AAA/CAA club office</a>.<p>

