<H3>Members Only Vacation Values:</H3>

<img align="right" width=284 height=185 src="hawship.gif" alt="Hawaii Ship">Take advantage of the exciting travel opportunities and discounts that come with your AAA membership.<p>

When you book your American Hawaii cruise vacation through a AAA Travel Agency, you can take advantage of these outstanding cruise offers:<p>

<UL>
<LI>April 1 - June 30, 1996 sailings<br>
       Receive a $100 per person shipboard credit.
       (value:  $200 per cabin)
<LI>July 1 - September 30, 1996 sailings<br>
       Receive a $50 per person shipboard credit.
       (value:  $100 per cabin)
<LI>October 1 - December 17, 1996 sailings<br>
       Enjoy a complimentary two night pre/post cruise Waikiki hotel package.
       <LI>(value:  $300 per couple)
</UL>

AAA member benefits apply to the first two full fare passengers in a cabin, are capacity controlled, and are available only through your AAA Travel Agency.<p>

<H3>About American Hawaii Cruises</H3>

<img align="left" width=176 height=267 src="hawfall.gif" alt="Hawaii water">An American Hawaii Cruises vacation is an ideal way to experience the unique attractions and natural wonders of the four major islands: lively Oahu, marvelous Maui, lush Kauai and the dramatic Big Island. On your 7-day cruise, you'll visit five ports of call on four beautiful islands ... and return with hundreds of cherished memories. Only by cruise ship can you see so much of so many islands, with so little effort. Unpack, relax and settle into your cabin for the week. Your ship is your floating hotel, sailing by night so you awake to new island adventures each day.<p>

Aboard ship, you'll enjoy delicious meals including Hawaiian specialties like Maui Mango Pasta and all-American favorites like filet mignon. In the evening, talented performers light up the state with their spirited songs and dance. Enjoy daily on-board activities, too, including hula lessons, games and more.<p>

American Hawaii Cruises owns and operates the world's only American-flagged, ocean-going passenger vessels. The <I>S.S. Independence</I> and the <I>S.S. Constitution</I> are staffed by American officers and crew, who are eager to welcome you into the relaxed, casual atmosphere of your ship.<br clear=all><p>
For additional information on this special travel value, contact your local <a href="aaaoffices.html">AAA/CAA club office</a>.<p>

