<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Crystal Cruises</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="classichawaii.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="deltaqueensteamboatco.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Crystal Cruises</h1></center>
<H3>Members Only Vacation Values:</H3>
<img align="right" width=248 height=146 src="crystalphoto1.gif" alt="crystalphoto1.gif">
Take advantage of the exciting travel opportunities and discounts that come with your AAA membership.<p>

When you book your Crystal cruise vacation through a AAA Travel Agency, you can select from a choice of ship and sailing dates to various locations which offer AAA percentage discounts of 10% - 35% off brochure rates.<p>

Single travelers can sail for only 15% more than the special discounted fares (excluding Penthouse Deck).<p>

Special "Perfect Harmony Fares" are offered on five sailings in 1996.  And, AAA members can receive a $100 per person shipboard credit on selected sailings.<p>

Ask your AAA travel agent about Crystal's Air/Sea program with low add-on airfare from $200-$600.<p>

<H3>About Crystal Cruises:</H3>
<img align="left" width=134 height=200 src="crystalphoto2.gif" alt="crystalphoto2.gif">

<i>Crystal Harmony</i> has been well received by its guests and was recognized almost immediately as a Five-Stars-Plus cruise experience.  Crystal Cruises was rated the Number One Large Luxury Cruise Ship by readers of Conde Nast Traveler magazine in 1993 and 1994; "Best Ship Overall" in 1992 and "Best Value" in 1993 and 1994 by Ocean and Cruise News.<p>

In addition, Berlitz Guide to Cruising consistently awarded the Five-Stars-Plus rating to both <i>Crystal Symphony</i> and <i>Crystal Harmony</i>.  And for 1996, Fielding's Guide to Worldwide Cruises has awarded Crystal Cruises an unprecedented Six-Stars.<p>

Described as the "best large luxury cruise ship experience in the world," <I>Crystal Harmony</I> and the new <I>Crystal Symphony</I> are like contemporary grand hotels afloat.  While cruise itineraries are developed to provide a balance of sea time and time on board, you'll find the ships a destination in and of themselves.<p>

For additional information on this special travel value, contact your local <a href="aaaoffices.html">AAA/CAA club office</a>.<p>
