<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Princess Cruises</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="pleasantholidays.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="royalcaribbeancruiselines.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Princess Cruises</h1></center>
<H3>Members Only Vacation Values:</H3>
<img align="right" width=237 height=138 src="princessphoto1.gif" alt="princessphoto1.gif">

Take advantage of the exciting travel opportunities and discounts that come with your AAA membership.<p>

As a AAA member, when you book your Princess Cruises vacation through a AAA Travel Agency, you can take advantages of these outstanding cruise offers.<p>

<UL>
<LI>Book one of the selected cruises from Princess' Panama Canal or Exotic Adventures brochures between May 15 and June 30 and receive an upgrade of two categories outside space or one category inside space.
<LI>Book one of the selected Caribbean sailings between August 15 and September 30 and receive an upgrade of one category inside or outside space and a $50 per cabin on-board credit.
<LI>Book one of the selected cruises to Alaska, Europe, Caribbean, or an Alaska Cruise Tour between November 15 and December 31 and receive an upgrade of two categories outside space or one category inside space.
</UL>

<H3>About Princess Cruises:</H3>
<img align="left" width=135 height=200 src="princessphoto2.gif" alt="princessphoto2.gif">

Princess Cruises, the original "Love Boats," sail more ships to more ports around the world than any other cruise line with over 150 different itineraries to over 200 ports of call.<p>

The Princess fleet of deluxe cruise ships just added another with the debut of the 77,000 gross ton superliner, the <I>Sun Princess</I>, in 1995, and more are on the way.  The <I>Dawn Princess</I> is set to sail in 1997, and the 104,000-gross-ton <I>Grand Princess</I> in 1998.<p>

Celebrating its 30th anniversary, Princess Cruises entertains its guests in grand style with original Broadway-style productions on its ships, including up to four different original Princess shows on a 7-day cruise.<p>

For additional information on this special travel value, contact your local <a href="aaaoffices.html">AAA/CAA club office</a>.<p>
<br clear=all>

