<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AAA and NAPA Offer Parts Program to Approved Repair Shops</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="strongbatteriesboostwinter.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="drivingcostsup7centin2n.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>AAA and NAPA Offer Parts Program to Approved Repair Shops</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., Sept. 16, 1996 -- The American Automobile Association and NAPA
have established a national parts program for repair facilities participating in
AAA's Approved Auto Repair program.
<p>
The AAA-NAPA parts program gives AAA-approved facilities stable, extremely
competitive prices on 185 product lines as well as a quarterly rebate on all
qualified parts purchases.
<p>
NAPA also offers AAA-approved facilities other benefits including a national
warranty, training opportunities, the NAPA Tech-Telediagnostic hotline,
changeover programs and seasonal marketing specials.
<p>
"This program gives approved shops an opportunity to increase sales and profit
while improving service to customers," said Paul Kindschy, director of AAA
National Road Service.  "For motorists, it means AAA-approved facilities will
use only the highest quality parts on their vehicles."
<p>
"The NAPA-AAA relationship teams the best auto repair facilities with their
local NAPA Auto Parts stores in a value-added relationship," said Ken Posey,
vice president, National Accounts for NAPA.  "We are proud to extend this
valuable offer to AAA-approved facilities."  
<p>
There is no cost for shops to enroll in the AAA-NAPA parts program.  Shops only
need to contact their local NAPA Auto Parts Store or register with their AAA
club.
<p>
The AAA Approved Auto Repair program currently recognizes more than 4,500
facilities in 31 states and the District of Columbia.  
<p>
NAPA was founded in 1925 and is the largest aftermarket supplier in the U.S.
with 73 NAPA distribution centers, 6,300 NAPA Auto Parts Stores, servicing all
50 states.
<p>
AAA news releases are now available on the Internet.  Within 15 minutes of
release, they will be available for download or fax through PRNewswire's site
Company News On Call.  The address is:
<a href="http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html">http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html</a>
and
the search word is AAA.  Releases will remain available until one year after the
release date.
<p>



