<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Break-downs can be time-consuming, costly and dangerous.</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="newcarsafetydevicesmaymea.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="donttakeachancewhenchoos.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Break-downs can be time-consuming, costly and dangerous.</h1></center>
<p>
A do-it-yourself monthly vehicle maintenance program can help prevent car
trouble before you get stuck, according to the American Automobile
Association.
<p>
Motorists can perform a simple 12-point check in about 30 minutes. Those who
do not could be plagued by starting problems or expensive repair bills, the
motoring federation said.
<p>
"Today's automobiles are a major investment and owners who neglect routine
maintenance procedures could be faced with expensive repair bills in the
future," said George Giek, managing director of AAA Automotive Services.
<p>
To help ensure improved year-round vehicle performance, motorists should
follow these simple maintenance procedures:
<p>
-  Check the antifreeze level and strength and inspect hoses and
connections for leaks and weak
   spots.
<p>
-  Use a commercial aerosol battery terminal cleaner to remove corrosion   on
terminals and cables. Then disconnect the terminals and clean the contact
surfaces with a wire brush and reconnect. Note: Disconnecting the battery may
cause your radio, accessories and engine computer to lose their memory and
the engine may take up to 50 minutes to run normally again. Inexpensive "keep
Alive" devices are available which plug into the cigarette lighter to prevent
memory loss.
<p>
-  Check the engine oil each time the car is filled with gasoline.
<p>
-  Replace the engine air filter every 25,000 miles. Replace it twice as
often if you drive on dirt or gravel roads.
<p>
-  Use the dipsticks to check the automatic transmission and power steering
fluids. Also check the brake fluid level.
<p>
-  Test the tension on the fan belt and look for fraying, glazing or
cracking.
<p>
-  Keep the windshield washer reservoir filled with solvent mixed to prevent
freezing.
<p>
-  Make sure all lights and turn signals work.
<p>
-  Check tire pressure regularly, including the spare, and inspect for
abnormal tread wear.
<p>

<p>


<center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="newcarsafetydevicesmaymea.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="donttakeachancewhenchoos.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
