<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Driving Costs Down Slightly In 3rd Quarter, AAA Says</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="newaaaprogramhelpsparents.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="markedwardstoleadaaatraff.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Driving Costs Down Slightly In 3rd Quarter, AAA Says</h1></center>
ORLANDO, Fla., Oct. 10 -- The cost of owning and operating a new car fell slightly in the third quarter, dropping .3 cent per mile, according to AAA.
<p>
Motorists now spend an average 43.1 cents per mile in vehicle-related costs, for a total of $6,465 for those who drive 15,000 annually.
<p>
The third-quarter decrease was primarily attributed to gasoline prices that fell 4.8 cents per gallon since June.
<p>
The first-quarter driving-cost estimate was 42.7 cents per mile.  Rising gasoline prices pushed the cost to 43.4 cents in the second quarter.
<p>
AAA's study of driving costs is updated quarterly from computations made by Runzheimer International of Rochester, Wisc.  The management consulting firm specializes in transportation, travel and living costs. 
<p>
The average per-mile cost is determined by combining operating and fixed costs.  During the third quarter of this year, motorists spent an average of 10.15 cents per mile on operating costs such as gasoline, oil, tires and maintenance, down .25 cent from March.  Fixed costs, including insurance, depreciation, registration, taxes and financing, averaged $13.56 per day, down 1 cent from March.
<p>
AAA's cost estimates are based on a composite national average of three domestically built cars:  a subcompact Ford Escort LX, a mid-size Ford Taurus GL and a full-size Chevrolet Caprice Classic.  
<p>
New England was the most expensive region in which to own and operate a car in the third quarter, with total costs of 45 cents per mile.  Midwest motorists had the lowest costs, paying 41.9 cents per mile.
<p>
Other regional costs were:  Mid-Atlantic, 43.8 cents; West, 43.9 cents; Southwest, 43.5 cents; Great Lakes, 42.3 cents; and  Southeast, 42 cents.
<p>
# # #
<p>
AAA news releases are now available on the Internet.  Within 15 minutes of release, they will be available for download or fax through PR Newswire's site Company News On Call.  The address is: http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html and the search word is AAA.  Releases will remain available until one year after the release date.


