<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AAA Credit Card Program Posts Strong Gains in 1995</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="financial.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaaselectspncbankasfinanc.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>AAA Credit Card Program Posts Strong Gains in 1995</h1></center>
<p>
SAN FRANCISCO, April 29, 1996 -- The AAA/VISA card and AAA/MasterCard credit
card program posted double-digit growth in several key performance areas in
1995, the American Automobile Association reported today.
<p>
AAA credit card transaction volume rose nearly 16 percent to $4.3 billion, up
from the previous year's $3.7 billion.  Outstanding balances jumped 21
percent, reaching $2.3 billion, compared to $1.9 billion in 1994.
<p>
Other gains were reported in the total number of AAA/VISA and AAA/MasterCard
credit cardholders, reaching 4 million in 1995 -- a 5 percent increase from
3.8 million card holders in 1994.
<p>
The AAA credit card program, introduced in 1978, was one of the first
affinity card programs in the United States.
<p>
Exclusive features of the AAA credit card include:  personal check-cashing
guarantee at participating AAA offices, no-fee American Express( Travelers
Cheques as a merchandise sale rather than a cash advance from AAA offices and
waiving the standard $50 liability clause if the AAA credit card is lost or
stolen and the issuing bank notified.
<p>
In other AAA financial services activity, the association's more than 1,000
offices in the U.S. and Canada sold $2.4 billion in American Express
Travelers Cheques in 1995, down from $2.5 billion in 1994.  The 5 percent
drop compares to an industry average decline of 8 percent.
<p>
Details of AAA's financial services performance were reported to more than
1,100 delegates during AAA's 93rd annual meeting in San Francisco.
<p>

<p>



