<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AAA Selects PNC Bank as Financial Services Partner</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="aaacreditcardprogramposts.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="fuelprices.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>AAA Selects PNC Bank as Financial Services Partner</h1></center>
<p>
HEATHROW, Fla., Jan. 30, 1996 -- The American Automobile Association today
announced the selection of PNC Bank Corp. (NYSE: PNC) to offer a broad range
of financial products and services to the AAA membership. 
<p>
Under the terms of the agreement, PNC Bank will provide a variety of
financial services through the newly formed AAA Financial Services
Corporation.
<p>
PNC Bank is one of the nation's largest financial services companies with
assets of more than $73 billion.
<p>
"AAA selected PNC Bank because of its strong commitment to customer service
and its technologically advanced banking operations, following an extensive
search that started last February," said AAA President Robert L. Darbelnet.
<p>
"This alliance is a key element in AAA's board-approved plan to offer an
expanded variety of favorably priced financial products and services
accessible by phone, mail and electronic delivery methods," Darbelnet said.
<p>
The program is targeted at AAA members in the United States and will build on
the success of AAA's credit card program which has nearly four million card
holders.  Product rollout -- including consumer loans, deposit accounts and
other card products -- is planned for August.
<p>
Service will be delivered through PNC Bank's National Financial Services
Center -- one of the leading and most sophisticated telebanking units in the
nation, with more than 500 financial representatives on staff.
<p>
"We are delighted to enter this long-term relationship with the nation's
premiere member service organization," said Thomas H. O'Brien, chairman and
CEO of PNC Bank Corp.
<p>
"PNC looks forward to working with the association to develop financial
products and services that will add significant value to the total AAA
membership package," O'Brien said.
<p>
AAA is a federation of 112 motor clubs providing its 39 million members in
the United States and Canada with a complete line of travel, insurance,
financial and auto-related services.
<p>
AAA Financial Services corp., jointly owned by participating AAA clubs and
AAA Inc., was formed in December to administer the Association's expanded
financial services program.  Darbelnet serves as chairman and CEO of an
eight-member board of directors composed of AAA club and association
executives.
<p>
PNC Bank Corp., headquartered in Pittsburgh, is one of the largest financial
services organizations in the U.S., with a strategic commitment to
alternative delivery of financial products and services.  Its major
businesses include corporate banking, consumer banking, mortgage banking and
asset management.
<p>



