<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>September Gas Prices Edge Up After 3-Month Drop, AAA Says</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="fuelprices.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="lowergaspricesawaitlabord.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>September Gas Prices Edge Up After 3-Month Drop, AAA Says</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., Sept. 17 -- After three months of falling gasoline prices,
motorists are paying slightly more at the pump in September, according to AAA.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Report shows the average price of self-serve regular
unleaded gasoline for September is $1.255 per gallon, up .2 cent from August.
<p>
This month's price is 8.7 cents higher than one year ago when the average was
1.168 per gallon.
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.306 per gallon,  2.8
cents more than last month and 4.3 cents higher than a year ago.  Self-serve
premium is $1.407, unchanged from a month ago and 6.5 cents more than last year.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.387 per gallon,
down .6 cent from last month and 12 cents higher than a year ago.  It is least
expensive in the Southeast at $1.17,  .3 cent less than a month ago and 7.6
cents more that last year. 
<p>
Other regional prices for self-serve are:  New England, $1.273 per gallon, down
1.7 cents in one month and 4.7 cents higher than last year; Mid-Atlantic,
$1.247, down 1 cent this month and up 7.5 cents from a year ago; Great Lakes,
$1.225, up 2.4 cents from last month and 9.4 cents higher than last year;
Midwest, $1.236, up 1.1 cents for the month and up 10.2 cents from a year ago;
and Southwest, $1.246, up 1.1 cents in one month and 9.1 cents higher than last
year.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the
last six months were:  August, 1.253, July, $1.274 per gallon; June, $1.303;
May, $1.307; April, $1.24; and March, $1.18.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in
September for the last five years were:  1995, $1.168 per gallon; 1994, $1.188;
1993, $1.082; 1992, $1.163 and 1991, $1.154.   
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn., which
publishes the National Petroleum Price Index that monitors more than 90,000
daily wholesale and retail prices in the United States and Canada.
<p>
AAA is a not-for-profit federation of 104 motor clubs with more than 1,000
offices providing 39 million members in the U.S. and Canada with travel,
insurance, financial and auto-related services.
<p>
###
AAA news releases are now available on the Internet.  Within 15 minutes of
release, they will be available for download or fax through PR Newswire's site
Company News On Call.  The address is:
<a href="http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html">http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html</a>
and
the search word is AAA.  Releases will remain available until one year after the
release date.
<p>



