<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gas Prices Down for Second Straight Month, Says AAA</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="lowergaspricesawaitlabord.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="gaspricesstabilizeafter3m.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Gas Prices Down for Second Straight Month, Says AAA</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., July 16, 1996 -- Gasoline prices continued to fall this month,
dropping nearly 3 cents per gallon since mid-June, according to the American
Automobile Association.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Report shows the average price of self-serve regular
unleaded gasoline is $1.274 per gallon for July, compared to $1.303 in June.
<p>

After rising 18.9 cents per gallon in the first five months of the year, the
price has fallen 3.3 cents in two months.
<p>
This month's price is 6.6 cents more than a year ago when gasoline averaged
$1.208 per gallon.  
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.364 per gallon,  2.8
cents less than last month.  Self-serve premium fell 2.9 cents to $1.445.
<p>
Full-service regular unleaded averages $1.509, down 1.9 cents from last
month.  Full-service mid-grade averages $1.609, down 1.4 cents.  Premium fell
2.2 cents to $1.664 per gallon.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.419 per
gallon, down 3.1 cents from last month.  It is least expensive in the
Southeast at $1.189, 2.7 cents less than a month ago. 
<p>
Other regional average prices are:  New England, $1.30 per gallon, down 2.8
cents in one month; Mid-Atlantic, $1.282, down 2.8 cents; Great Lakes,
$1.242, down 3.3 cents; Midwest, $1.23, down 2.8 cents; and Southwest,
$1.258, down 2.9 cents.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the
last six months were:  June, $1.303 per gallon; May, $1.307; April, $1.24;
March, $1.18; February, $1.129; and January, $1.139.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in June
for the last five years were:  1995, $1.208 per gallon; 1994, $1.143; 1993,
$1.111; 1992, $1.166; and 1991, $1.139.   
<p>
Thirty-eight percent of the stations surveyed will operate 24 hours.
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn.,
which publishes the National Petroleum Price Index that monitors more than
90,000 daily wholesale and retail prices in the United States and Canada.
<p>

<p>


