<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gas Prices Stabilize After 3-Month Rise, Says AAA</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="gaspricesdownforsecondstr.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="gaspricesrise67centsino.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Gas Prices Stabilize After 3-Month Rise, Says AAA</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., June 18 -- After three months of rising gas prices, relief may
be in sight as the average price slipped nearly a half cent per gallon in the
last month, according to the American Automobile Association.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Survey shows the average price of self-serve regular
unleaded gasoline is $1.303 per gallon for June, compared to $1.307 in May.
<p>
This month's price is 7.5 cents more than a year ago when gasoline averaged
$1.228 per gallon.
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.392 per gallon,  .5
cent less than last month.  Self-serve premium fell .4 cent to $1.474.
<p>
Full-service regular unleaded averages $1.528, down .2 cent from last month.
Full-service mid-grade averages $1.623, down .3 cent.  Premium fell .1 cent
to $1.686 per gallon.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.450 per
gallon, down .1 cent from last month.  It is least expensive in the Southeast
at $1.216, 2 cents less than a month ago.
<p>
Other regional average prices are:  New England, $1.328 per gallon, down .1
cent in one month; Mid-Atlantic, $1.310, up .3 cent; Great Lakes, $1.275,
down .3 cent; Midwest, $1.258, up .7 cent; and Southwest, $1.287, down 1.2
cents.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the
last six months were:  May, $1.307 per gallon; April, $1.24; March, $1.18;
February, $1.129; January, $1.139; and December, $1.118.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in June
for the last five years were:  1995, $1.228; 1994, $1.115; 1993, $1.123;
1992, $1.184; and 1991, $1.162.
<p>
Seventy-eight percent of the stations surveyed will be open over the holiday
and 38 percent will operate 24 hours.
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn.,
which publishes the National Petroleum Price Index that monitors more than
90,000 daily wholesale and retail prices in the United States and Canada.
<p>
AAA is a not-for-profit federation of 106 motor clubs with more than 1,000
offices providing 39 million members in the U.S. and Canada with travel,
insurance, financial and auto-related services.
<p>


