<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gas Prices Rise 6.7 Cents in One Month, AAA says</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="gaspricesstabilizeafter3m.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaaoffers10tipsforcutting.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Gas Prices Rise 6.7 Cents in One Month, AAA says</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., May 14, 1996 -- Motorists are finding the highest gas prices
in 15 years as the average price increased 6.7 cents per gallon in the last
month, according to the American Automobile Association.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Survey shows the average price of self-serve regular
unleaded gasoline is $1.307 per gallon, 11.1 cents more than a year ago.
Prices have jumped 17.8 cents in the last three months.
<p>
This month's price is the highest pre-Memorial Day figure since 1981 when
gasoline averaged $1.377 per gallon.
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.397 per gallon,  6.4
cents more than last month.  Self-serve premium increased 6.6 cents to
$1.478.
<p>
Full-serve regular unleaded averages $1.53 per gallon, up 5.6 cents from last
month.  Full-serve mid-grade averages $1.626, up 5.4 cents.  Premium rose 6
cents to $1.687.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.451 per
gallon, up 12.6 cents from last month.  It is least expensive in the
Southeast at $1.236, 5.6 cents more than a month ago.
<p>
Other regional average prices are:  New England, $1.329 per gallon, up 8.7
cents in one month; Mid-Atlantic, $1.307,  up 8.1 cents; Great Lakes, $1.278,
up 3.4 cents; Midwest, $1.251, up 2.7 cents; and Southwest, $1.299, up 5.9
cents.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the
last six months were: April, $1.24 per gallon, March, $1.18; February,
$1.129; January, $1.139; December, $1.118; and November, $1.123.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in May
for the last five years were: 1995, $1.196 per gallon; 1994, $1.105; 1993,
$1.132; 1992, $1.139; and 1991, $1.161.
<p>
Seventy-six percent of the stations surveyed will be open over the holiday
and 38 percent will operate 24 hours.
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn.,
which publishes the National Petroleum Price Index that monitors more than
90,000 daily wholesale and retail prices in the United States and Canada.
<p>


