<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gas Prices Hit Highest Point Since Gulf War</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="aaaoffers10tipsforcutting.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="gaspricesupsharplyforeast.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Gas Prices Hit Highest Point Since Gulf War</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., April 16, 1996 -- Gasoline prices continued their upward
charge as the average price of self-serve regular unleaded reached the
highest level since January 1991 during the start of Operation
Desert Storm, according to the American Automobile Association.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Survey shows the average price of self-serve regular
unleaded gasoline is $1.24 per gallon, up 6 cents from the previous month and
11.1 above February's price.  In January 1991, the gasoline
averaged $1.249.
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.333 per gallon, 6.1
cents more than last month.  Self-serve premium increased 5.9 cents to
$1.412.
<p>
Full-serve regular unleaded averages $1.474 per gallon, up 4.5 cents from
last month.  Full-serve mid-grade averages $1.572, up 4 cents.  Premium rose
4.1 cents to $1.627.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.325 per
gallon, up 7.2 cents from last month.  It is least expensive in the Southeast
at $1.18, 6.5 cents more than a month ago.
<p>
Other regional average prices are:  New England, $1.242 per gallon, up 5.1
cents in one month; Mid-Atlantic, $1.226,  up 6.2 cents; Great Lakes, $1.244,
up 5.5 cents; Midwest, $1.224, up 6.4 cents; and Southwest, $1.24, up 5.4
cents.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the
last six months were: March, $1.18 per gallon; February, $1.129; January,
$1.139; December, $1.118; November, $1.123; and October, $1.154.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in April
for the last five years were: 1995, $1.128 per gallon; 1994, $1.086; 1993,
$1.118; 1992, $1.082; and 1991, $1.119.
<p>
Nearly 37 percent of the stations surveyed are open 24 hours.
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn.,
which publishes the National Petroleum Price Index that monitors more than
90,000 daily wholesale and retail prices in the United States and
Canada.
<p>
AAA is a not-for-profit federation of 112 motor clubs with more than 1,000
offices providing nearly 39 million members in the United States and Canada
with travel, insurance, financial and auto-related services.
<p>

<p>



