<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gas Prices Up Sharply for Easter and Passover Travel</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="gaspriceshithighestpoints.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="gaspricesup21centsfirs.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Gas Prices Up Sharply for Easter and Passover Travel</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., March 26, 1996 -- Motorists traveling for early spring
holidays will find gasoline prices up more than a nickel per gallon from a
month ago, according to the American Automobile Association.
<p>
According to AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Survey, the price of self-serve
regular unleaded gasoline is $1.18 per gallon -- up 5.1 cents in one month
and 5.2 cents more than at last year's Easter and Passover holidays.
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.272 per gallon,  4.8
cents more than last month.  Self-serve premium increased 4.6 cents to
$1.353.
<p>
Full-serve regular unleaded averages $1.429 per gallon, up 3.7 cents from
last month.  Full-serve mid-grade averages $1.532, up 3.7 cents.  Premium
rose 3.5 cents to $1.586.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.253 per
gallon, up 2.4 cents from last month.  It is least expensive in the
Southeast at $1.115, 6.1 cents more than a month ago.
<p>
Other regional average prices are:  New England, $1.191 per gallon, up 1.6
cents in one month; Mid-Atlantic, $1.164 up 3.7 cents; Great Lakes, $1.189,
up 7.8 cents; Midwest, $1.16, up 5.8 cents; and Southwest, $1.186, up 7.8
cents.
<p>
Nearly 38 percent of the stations surveyed will be open 24 hours and 71
percent will be open on the Easter holiday.
<p>
The survey was conducted by Computer Petroleum Corp. of St. Paul, Minn.,
which publishes the National Petroleum Price
Index that monitors more than  90,000 daily wholesale and retail prices in
the United States and Canada.
<p>
 AAA is a not-for-profit federation of 112 motor clubs with more than 1,000
offices providing nearly 39 million members in the U.S. and Canada with
travel, insurance, financial and auto-related services.
<p>


