<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Autumn Gas Prices Refuse To Fall, AAA Says</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="gaspricesup21centsfirs.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="highergaspricestogreettha.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Autumn Gas Prices Refuse To Fall, AAA Says</h1></center>
ORLANDO, Fla., Oct. 15, 1996 -- The national average price of gasoline edged up nearly half a cent per gallon in October and is more than a dime than higher than one year ago, according to AAA.
<p>
AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Report shows the average price of self-serve regular unleaded gasoline is $1.259 per gallon, up  .4 cent from September.  In the past two months, the price has risen .6 cent per gallon.
<p>
This month's price is 10.5 cents higher than last October, when the average was 1.154 per gallon.
<p>
The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.353 per gallon, 4.7 cents more than last month and 10.5 cents higher than a year ago.  Self-serve premium is $1.414, .7 cent higher than a month ago and 8.5 cents more than last year.
<p>
Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.385 per gallon, down .2 cent from last month and 12 cents higher than a year ago.  It is least expensive in the Southeast at $1.181,  1.1 cents more than a month ago and 10.6 cents more that last year. 
<p>
Other regional prices for self-serve are:  New England, $1.271 per gallon, down .2 cent in one month and 5.3 cents higher than last year; Mid-Atlantic, $1.256, down .9 cent this month and up 10.2 cents from a year ago; Great Lakes, $1.227, up .2 cents from last month and 10.8 cents higher than last year; Midwest, $1.236, unchanged the month and up 12.3 cents from a year ago; and Southwest, $1.259, up 1.3 cents in one month and 12.5 cents higher than last year.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the last six months were:  September, $1.255 per gallon; August, $1.253; July, $1.274; June, $1.303; May, $1.307; and April, $1.24.
<p>
The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in October for the last five years were:  1995, $1.154 per gallon; 1994, $1.157; 1993, $1.134; 1992, $1.156 and 1991, $1.128.

