<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Higher Gas Prices To Greet Thanksgiving Travelers</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="autumngaspricesrefusetofa.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="holidaygaspricescontinueto.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Higher Gas Prices To Greet Thanksgiving Travelers</h1></center>
ORLANDO, Fla.,  Nov. 19, 1996 -- Motorists traveling for the Thanksgiving holiday will find gasoline prices up 1.8 cents per gallon from October and 15.4 cents higher than a year ago, according to AAA.  <p>

AAA's monthly Fuel Gauge Report shows the average price of self-serve regular unleaded gasoline is $1.277 per gallon -- the highest for a Thanksgiving holiday since 1990, when the price was $1.359 per gallon.<p>

The average price of self-serve mid-grade unleaded is $1.355 per gallon, .2 cent more than last month and 13.7 cents above a year ago.  Self-serve premium is $1.431, 1.7 cents higher than a month ago and 13.2 cents more than last year.<p>

Self-serve regular unleaded is most expensive in the West at $1.366 per gallon, down 1.9 cents from last month and 11.2 cents higher than a year ago.  It is least expensive in the Southeast at $1.204,  2.3 cents more than a month ago and 16.6 cents more than last year. <p>

Other regional prices for self-serve are:  New England, $1.293 per gallon, up 2.2 cents in one month and 11 cents higher than last year; Mid-Atlantic, $1.281, up 2.5 cents this month and up 16.1 cents from a year ago; Great Lakes, $1.282, up 5.5 cents from last month and 20.2 cents higher than last year; Midwest, $1.259, up 2.3 cents this month and up 18.1 cents from a year ago; and Southwest, $1.251, down .8 cent in one month and 14.4 cents more than last year.<p>

The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline for the last six months were:  October, 1.259 per gallon; September, $1.255; August, $1.253; July, $1.274; June, $1.303; and May, $1.307.<p>

The national average prices for self-serve regular unleaded gasoline in November for the last five years were:  1995, $1.123 per gallon; 1994, $1.165; 1993, $1.116; 1992, $1.157 and 1991, $1.143.   <p>

AAA news releases are now available on the Internet.  Within 15 minutes of release, they will be available for download or fax through PR Newswire's site Company News On Call.  The address is: http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html and the search word is AAA.  Releases will remain available until one year after the release date.

