<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AAA Elects Officers at 93rd Annual Meeting</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="news.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="hayesnamedmanagingdirector.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>AAA Elects Officers at 93rd Annual Meeting</h1></center>
<p>
SAN FRANCISCO, April 30, 1996 -- Van P. Smith, an Indiana business and civic
leader, was re-elected chairman of the 39-million-member American Automobile
Association at the 93rd AAA Annual meeting here today.
<p>
The more than 1,100 delegates and club officials, representing the federation's
112 motor clubs in the United States and Canada, also re-elected Terry W. Baker
of Portland, Ore., vice chairman, and Dwight D. Sutherland of Kansas City, Mo.,
secretary.
<p>
The AAA meeting is being held at the San Francisco Marriott.
<p>
Smith, chairman of the Ontario Corp. in Muncie, Ind., serves as chairman of the
Colgate University Board of Trustees and is a past chairman of the U.S. Chamber
of Commerce.  He has been a director the AAA Hoosier Motor Club since 1980 and
is presently that club's vice chairman.
<p>
Baker is a founding partner of the law firm of Tonkon, Torp, Galen, Marmaduke
and Booth in Portland, Ore.  The 1962 college football Heisman Trophy winner and
member of the College Football Hall of Fame has been a director of AAA Oregon
since 1988.
<p>
Sutherland is a partner and chief executive officer of the largest privately
owned retail lumber company in the U.S. and has been a director of AAA Missouri
since 1986.
<p>
Elected to new three-year terms on the board of directors were:  Waldo H.
Burnside of Los Angeles, Calif., and Ronald L. Steffens of Dearborn, Mich.
<p>
Re-elected to three-year terms on the board were:  Smith; Baker; Marquerite
Dispenza Hambleton of Buffalo, N.Y.; Charles H. Hire of Columbus, Ohio; and
Edward L. Jones, Jr. of Philadelphia, Pa.
<p>
Marilyn M. Pfaltz of Summit, N.Y., was elected to a two-year term.  Sutherland
and Wayne L. Hooey of Toronto, Ont., Canada, were elected to one-year terms.
<p>
Officers and directors assume duties immediately upon election.


