<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Hayes Named Managing Director for AAA Public Relations</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="aaaelectsofficersat93rdan.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="healthygainswithtravelpart.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Hayes Named Managing Director for AAA Public Relations</h1></center>
<p>
WASHINGTON, D.C., Jan. 2 -- Stephen D. Hayes, who has served as public affairs
director for three large Federal agencies, has been named managing director of
public relations for the American Automobile Association, effective Jan. 16.
<p>
Hayes will be based here at AAA's public and government relations office. He
will also direct public relations activities and provide promotional support for
AAA business lines at the 38-million-member association's Orlando, Fla., area
national office.
<p>
Hayes, who has an extensive background working with the electronic and print
media in both the public and private sectors, has been communications director
for U.S. Sen. Thad Cochran, R-Miss., since January 1995.
<p>
He served previously as director, Office of Public Affairs for the U.S. Agency
for International Development; was assistant administrator for public affairs
for the Federal Aviation Administration; and was director of public affairs and
special assistant to the commissioner of the Internal Revenue Service.
<p>
Hayes also has been a speech writer and media spokesperson
for several Federal agencies.
<p>
In the private sector, Hayes was senior vice president for Asian Operations,
Gannon Pacific Co. in Reston, Va., and was vice president of communications for
the Air Transport Association.
<p>
As a U.S. naval officer, Hayes received a number of honors during the Vietnam
conflict, including the Navy Bronze Star and the Navy Commendation Medal for
heroism in combat.
<p>
A native of Delaware, he graduated from Dartmouth University with a B.A. in
philosophy and from Georgetown University with an M.A. in government and
international relations.
<p>
He lives in Alexandria, Va., with his wife, Barbara and their two children.
<p>


