<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Healthy Gains with Travel Partners Boost AAA Travel Agency Sales</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="hayesnamedmanagingdirector.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="ahistoryofservice.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>Healthy Gains with Travel Partners Boost AAA Travel Agency Sales</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla, March 4 -- Propelled by a 59 percent jump in preferred supplier
sales, AAA's total travel agency sales exceeded $2.15 billion in 1995, up 10
percent from 1994, the American Automobile Association reported today.
<p>
"While many in the industry experienced flat or modest gains, our cruise and
tour partners reported double, even triple- digit increases in 1995 with AAA
travel agencies," said Jack Mannix, managing director, AAA Travel Related
Services.
<p>
Last year AAA reduced the number of preferred travel suppliers from more than
400 to 26 partners in a move to enhance the benefits package for AAA's more than
38 million members.
<p>
"AAA travel agency managers and staff, along with a smaller but stronger team of
travel partners, have proven that `more is not always better'," Mannix said.
<p>
AAA travel agencies reported the following sales activity in 1995 compared to
1994:
- Tour sales exceeded $450 million, an 18 percent gain;
- Cruise sales jumped to $300 million, a 12 percent increase;
- Air sales neared $1.13 billion, up more than 4 percent;
- Total car-rental sales through AAA travel agencies increased to $95.2 million,
up more than 18 percent;
- Sales of other AAA travel agency services, including motorcoach, rail and
hotel, accounted for $175.7 million.
<p>


