<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>54 Million Leisure Travelers to Benefit from AAA-Thomas Cook Alliance</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="travel.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaaofferstipsforairtravel.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>54 Million Leisure Travelers to Benefit from AAA-Thomas Cook Alliance</h1></center>
<p>
VIENNA, Austria, Sept. 9, 1996 -- AAA and Thomas Cook, two of the most
recognized names in travel, today announced plans to form the world's largest
leisure travel alliance, pending U.S. regulatory clearance.
<p>
The global network will join Thomas Cook's 1,800 offices with AAA's 1,000 travel
agency locations to serve a combined customer base of more than 54 million
leisure travelers.
<p>
The alliance, which becomes fully operational Jan. 1, 1997, provides all leisure
travelers who make international travel arrangements through AAA access to the
Thomas Cook Worldwide Customer Promise.  AAA will provide reciprocal services to
Thomas Cook customers in the United States.
<p>
Benefits of the Worldwide Customer Promise include the following no-fee services
for the leisure traveler: airline reservation changes, ticket revalidation or
rerouting, hotel and car rental reservations, changes to travel arrangements,
travel planning and emergency local telephone call assistance.  
<p>
In addition to enhanced customer service, the AAA-Thomas Cook alliance will
focus aggressively on the development and implementation of new travel-related
technology applications and electronic distribution channels.
<p>
The first joint project in the technology arena will begin in January when AAA
joins the Catalist Trading Exchange, an electronic leisure travel booking system
developed by Thomas Cook, which integrates into AAA's new AVATAR system. 
Catalist allows travel counselors to electronically create customized vacations
for independent or group travel to destinations worldwide.
<p>
"AAA's alliance with Thomas Cook allows the association to deliver unparalleled
customer service far beyond its borders," said Graeme Clarke, senior vice
president, AAA Products & Services.  "Today's announcement  provides AAA members
the same level of security and peace-of-mind whether they are visiting Boston,
Britain or Beijing."
<p>
"With AAA's extensive network in the U.S. and Thomas Cook's presence in the rest
of the world, this alliance is a perfect geographic and strategic fit for both
companies," said Mark McCafferty, managing director, Worldwide Travel-Related
Businesses, The Thomas Cook Group.
<p>
"Customers of both organizations can look forward to many new and exciting
benefits as a result of two of the world's leading brands in travel working
together," McCafferty said. 
<p>
Future initiatives will include negotiations with multi-national level suppliers
and cooperative ventures in the foreign exchange and publishing arenas.
<p>
AAA is a federation of 106 motor clubs providing its 39 million members in the
U.S. and Canada with a full line of travel, financial, insurance and
automotive-related services.
<p>
Thomas Cook has been serving customers for 155 years.  Today the Group employs
over 12,000 people who serve some 20 million customers a year with two core
business lines -- financial services and travel-related  businesses.
<p>
#  #  # 
<p>
AAA news releases are now available on the Internet.  Within 15 minutes of
release, they will be available for download or fax through PR Newswire's site
Company News On Call.  The address is:
<a href="http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html">http://www.prnewswire.com/cnoc.html</a>
and
the search word is AAA.  Releases will remain available until one year after the
release date.


