<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AAA, Industry Leaders Gather In Vienna To Explore A Brand New World Of Travel</TITLE></HEAD><BODY LINK="#0000bf" VLINK="#ee0000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="aaatile.gif"><center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><TR><TD><a href="labordaytravelexpectedtoi.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="prev.gif" alt="PREV"></a></TD><TD><a href="welcome.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="home.gif" alt="HOME"></a></TD><TD><a href="index.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="navigate.gif" alt="Navigate"></a></TD><TD><a href="aaaselectsthreeairlinesto.html"><img align="middle" border=0 width=100 height=40 src="next.gif" alt="NEXT"></a></TD></TR>
</table><h1>AAA, Industry Leaders Gather In Vienna To Explore A Brand New World Of Travel</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., Aug. 21, 1996 -- Global alliances, brand management and travel
technology will take center stage at the 1996 AAA Travel Industry Conference in
Vienna, Austria from Sept. 8-11.
<p>
"This conference promises to explore 'a brand new world' for AAA and for the
travel agency community," said Jack E. Mannix, managing director, AAA Travel
Related Services. 
<p>
"We will be looking at new products, new alliances and a new brand awareness
campaign that will take AAA far beyond the turn of the century."
<p>
More than 400 AAA club CEOs, club travel executives and travel industry leaders
are registered to attend AAA's international event held at the Vienna Hilton.
<p>
In addition to AAA executives addressing the delegation, the following industry
leaders will examine a variety of travel-related issues during general sessions: 
Frank Olson, chairman, The Hertz Corporation; Tom Elrod, president-entertainment
& marketing, Walt Disney Attractions; Bob Dickinson, president, Carnival Cruise
Lines; Judy Bishop, vice president-North American sales, United Airlines; Dr.
Marc Mancini, consultant.
<p>
Panel discussions will include: Maureen Van Metter, vice president-sales
administration, Trafalgar Tours; John Molinaro, vice president-national sales,
Princess Cruises; Lynne Rosenbaum, senior vice president-marketing, Apollo
Travel Services; Jerry Healey, vice president-sales, Pleasant Holidays; Linda
Ehlenberger, vice president-field sales, Holland America Line-Westours; Richard
Friese, publisher, Travel Agent Magazine.
<p>
Other industry panelists include: Paul Blackney, president, Apollo Travel
Services; Dave Hilfman, staff vice president-national sales; Continental
Airlines; Brian Kennedy, executive vice president-sales & marketing, Hertz; Ron
Letterman, president, Classic Custom Vacations. 
<p>
Workshop sessions will be led by the following industry executives:  Jeff
Miller, attorney; Joe Exum, managing director-AAA Vacations, Certified
Vacations; Bob Joselyn, president, Robert Joselyn & Associates; Marc Rosenberg,
president, Galileo Canada.
</PRE></HTML>


