</table><h1>AAA Announces 1997-1998 Preferred Supplier Team</h1></center>
<p>
ORLANDO, Fla., July 26, 1996 -- The American Automobile Association has named
23 cruise and tour partners to its preferred supplier team for the 1997-1998
program.  (See attached list.)
<p>
"These partners have consistently demonstrated their commitment to the AAA
organization and to our 39 million members," said Jack E. Mannix, managing
director, AAA Travel Related Services.  
<p>
"In addition, AAA and Canadian Automobile Association clubs have fully
embraced the powerful lineup of preferred suppliers.  With a  59 percent
increase in preferred supplier sales in the first year alone, we have shown
that we can move market share, plus grow the business." 
<p>
The 1997-1998 selection process involved the following club executives:  John
Connors, Automobile Club of Western and Central New York; Bill Figge,
Automobile Club of Southern California; Steve Frank, AAA Minneapolis;
Jennifer McMutrie, Auto Club South; and AAA national office representatives.
<p>
Also providing input to the Preferred Supplier Review Committee was a
44-member preferred supplier account executive team that was involved in the
supplier year-end evaluations.
<p>
Proposals were sent to all existing AAA preferred tour and cruise suppliers
and addressed 28 areas including:  member benefits, improved commissions and
overrides, training, enhanced service relationship, sales and marketing
support and complaint resolution.  The final selection of the 1997-1998
preferred suppliers was based on the overall performance of AAA's 23 partners
in those primary areas.
<p>
AAA's 1997-1998 cruise and tour suppliers bring a wealth of value-added
member benefits, plus an aggressive investment in sales and marketing support
and an enhanced commission structure to AAA and CAA travel agencies.
<p>
No additional travel partners have been added to the 1997-1998 preferred
supplier lineup as the majority of world-wide destinations were covered by
AAA's current partners at an increased level. 
<p>
In 1995, AAA reduced the number of preferred travel suppliers from more than
400 to 26 partners in a move to enhance the association's member benefits
package.
<p>
AAA is a federation of 106 motor clubs providing its members in the United
States and Canada with comprehensive travel, insurance, financial and auto
related services.
<p>
                        AAA PREFERRED CRUISE SUPPLIERS
Alaska Sightseeing/Cruisewest
American Hawaii Cruises
Carnival Cruise Lines
Crystal Cruises
The Delta Queen Steamboat Co.
